/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3449.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now my heart turned to water in my breast.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3453.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Could he have heard?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3454.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And how dared I go before the Lion bearing his living child hidden on my back?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3460.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|to show fear was to be lost,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3462.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|to disobey was to be lost.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3464.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Good!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3465.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I come,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3466.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was sundown.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3467.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and so I stayed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3468.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|having royal blood on my hands,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3470.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till the king has pardoned me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3472.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I pointed to the mat in my hand.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3475.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let me look at it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3476.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"He might have been a king,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3477.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Mopo, thou hast slain one who might have been a king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3481.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Art thou not afraid?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3483.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"No, Black One,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3484.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3485.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the child is killed by order of one who is a king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3488.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Sit down, and let us talk,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3490.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|To-morrow thou shalt have five oxen for this deed;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3493.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thou shalt choose them from the royal herd.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3495.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The king is good;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3496.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he sees that my belt is drawn tight;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3499.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he satisfies my hunger.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_35.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as already it was great among many another tribe,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3501.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Will the king suffer that I go?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3503.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My wife is in labour and I would visit her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3505.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Did she weep when you took the babe from her?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3508.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Had she wept she had been slain also.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3511.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Who was with her?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3512.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The Mother of the Heavens.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3514.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|By myself I swear, though she is my mother-if I thought
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3518.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he ceased.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3520.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There was a silence, then he spoke again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3522.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Medicine, king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3523.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3524.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I tell you that the marrow melted in my bones with terror,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3529.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he answered angrily.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_353.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|His name does not matter, for he plays no part in this story.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3531.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|What?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3532.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who am the first of doctors?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3534.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Death is the king's medicine,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3535.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3536.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I bent over it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3538.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|while the sweat of terror ran down my face blinding me like tears.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3542.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|What if the child awoke and cried?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3545.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yes, I would kill the king and then kill myself!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3548.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Ugly stuff,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3549.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the king, taking snuff.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3552.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But as he threw,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3553.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and did not touch the child.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3555.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"May the heavens bless the king!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3557.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I said, according to custom.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3559.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Thanks to thee, Mopo, it is a good omen,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_356.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which he was transporting to Pretoria.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3562.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3563.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Take my advice:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3564.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|kill thy children, as I kill mine, lest they live to worry thee.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3568.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The whelps of lions are best drowned.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3571.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I did up the bundle fast-fast, though my hands trembled.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3575.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|what if the child should wake and cry.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3577.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was done; I rose and saluted the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_358.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The weather was cold and there was little or no grass for the oxen,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3581.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I doubled myself up and passed from before him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3584.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|If it had been one minute before!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3586.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3587.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Girdle composed of skin and tails of oxen.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3590.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I have recovered the child, women,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3592.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I said, as I undid the bundle.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3594.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"The boy seems bigger than he was,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3596.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she said.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3597.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"The breath of life has come into him and puffed him out,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3600.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3601.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"His eyes are not as his eyes were,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3603.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she said again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3604.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now they are big and black, like the eyes of the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3607.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3608.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"This child has a birth-mark on his thigh,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3611.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I laid my medicine there,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3613.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3614.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"It is not the same child,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3615.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she said sullenly.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3617.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I rose up in my rage and cursed her heavily,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_362.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which made the journey difficult;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3620.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I saw that if she was not stopped this woman's tongue would bring us all to ruin.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3625.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Do you wish to draw down a curse upon our roof?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3628.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Would you make us all food for the king's spear?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3631.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So I stormed on,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3633.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|threatening to bring her to death,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3635.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till at length she grew fearful,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3637.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and fell at my feet praying for mercy and forgiveness.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_364.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but he had been tempted to it by the high rates of transport that prevailed at that season of the year,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3641.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I was much afraid because of this woman's tongue,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3644.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and not without reason.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3647.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nothing more was heard of it, but still it only slept;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3650.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and, my father, I feared greatly for the hour when it should awake.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3654.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Mother of the Heavens,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3655.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So it happened that very often one or the other of them would come into my hut,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3660.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and take the boy upon her lap and fondle it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3663.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In vain did I pray them to forbear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3665.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Love pulled at their heart-strings more heavily than my words,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3669.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and still they came.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3670.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he asked of me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3672.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Cannot she kiss me, if she will find a child to kiss?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3675.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And he laughed like a wolf.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3677.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|afraid of nothing.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3678.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In all the world there were but two people whom he loved-these were I,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3683.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Mopo,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3684.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who was called his father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3686.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she who was said to be his twin sister.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3688.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|her eyes were softer and larger than those of our people,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_369.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which would remunerate him for any probable loss he might suffer in cattle.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3691.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|her hair longer and less tightly curled,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3694.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and her skin was lighter-more of the colour of pure copper.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3698.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|than any woman of my people whom I have seen.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3701.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|was of Swazi blood,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3702.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and given to me as a wife by the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3705.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was said that she was the daughter of a Swazi headman of the tribe of the Halakazi,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3710.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and that she was born of his wife is true,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3712.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but whether he was her father I do not know;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3715.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He was a Portuguese from the coast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3717.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a handsome man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3718.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and skilled in the working of iron.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3720.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At least I know this,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3721.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But none can tell the truth of these matters,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3724.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I only speak of them because the beauty of Nada was rather as is the beauty of the white people than of ours,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_373.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So he pushed along on his journey,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3731.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and this might well happen if her grandfather chanced to be a white man.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3735.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Together they ate, together they slept and wandered;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3739.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The first time it came about thus.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3741.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|On they wandered and on,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3742.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|singing as they went,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3743.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then it was near sundown, and when they had eaten they fell asleep.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3747.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for it was the beginning of winter,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3749.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|when fruits are ripe.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3750.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|frightened,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3751.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and hand in hand they stumbled through the darkness.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3754.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But in the wind and the night they lost their path,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3757.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and when at length the dawn came they were in a forest that was strange to them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_376.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and all went well until he had passed the little town of Stanger,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3762.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They rested awhile, and finding berries ate them, then walked again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3766.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|All that day they wandered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3767.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they were so weary that they fell asleep in each other's arms.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3771.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At dawn they rose,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3773.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but now they were very tired and berries were few,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3776.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that by midday they were spent.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3778.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then they lay down on the side of a steep hill,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3781.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Here let us die, my brother,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3783.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she said.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3784.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But even then the boy had a great spirit, and he answered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3787.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Time to die, sister, when Death chooses us.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3790.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|See, now!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3791.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Do you rest here, and I will climb the hill and look across the forest.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3795.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So he left her and climbed the hill,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3797.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and filled himself with them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3799.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At length he came to the crest of the hill and looked out across the sea of green.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_38.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the royal salute,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_380.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The night after he left Stanger the air turned bitterly cold,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3803.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3804.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|far away to the east,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3805.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he saw a line of white that lay like smoke against the black surface of a cliff,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3810.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he found that her senses had left her through hunger,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3813.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She lay upon the ground like one asleep,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3816.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and over her stood a jackal that fled as he drew nigh.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3819.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet he found a third,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3821.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he made ropes of them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3822.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He could never have reached it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3824.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet at evening some messengers running through the forest came upon a naked lad with a girl bound to his back and a staff in his hand,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_383.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and hid the light of the stars.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3832.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who staggered along slowly with starting eyes and foam upon his lips.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3837.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He could not speak,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3838.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he was so weary,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3839.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the ropes had cut through the skin of his shoulders;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3842.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the son of Mopo,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3844.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thinking her dead,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3845.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but he pointed to her breast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3847.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they found that her heart still beat,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3849.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so they brought her also;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_385.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I should say that there was a heavy fall of snow coming,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3851.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and not lead his sister to the wilds.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3853.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But the boy loved roaming like a fox,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3855.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and where he went there Nada followed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3858.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and sought out a certain deep glen which had an evil name,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3862.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Whether this was true I do not know,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3864.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I know that in the glen dwelt a certain woman of the woods,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3867.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who had her habitation in a cave and lived upon what she could kill or steal or dig up with her hands.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3873.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|by the witch-doctors as a worker of magic against the king, and slain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3878.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|according to custom,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3879.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|three young girls,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_388.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the White Man to himself.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3880.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So she fled and took up her abode in the haunted glen;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3884.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and this was the nature of her madness,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3887.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that whenever she saw children,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3888.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and more especially girl children,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3891.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a longing came upon her to kill them as her own had been killed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3895.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she did often,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3896.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for when the moon was full and her madness at its highest,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_39.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Why did you do this, my father?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_390.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have often seen the sky look like that in Scotland before snow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3900.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she would travel far to find children,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3903.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|none would touch her because of the spirit in her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3906.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|not even those whose children she had murdered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3909.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and sat down by a pool of water not far from the mouth of her cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3913.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|weaving flowers into a garland.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3915.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|As he went he called back to her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3917.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and his voice awoke the woman who was sleeping in her cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3921.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|smelling blood and having a spear in her hand.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3924.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently she saw Nada seated upon the grass weaving flowers,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3928.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now as she came-so the child told me-suddenly a cold wind seemed to breathe upon Nada,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3935.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though she did not see the woman who would murder her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3938.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and there,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3939.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who crept down upon her from above,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_394.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he reflected that there had been no deep snow in Natal for years,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3941.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|her hair hanging about her brow and her eyes shining like the eyes of a lion.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3947.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He turned and rushed back over the brow of the hill, and, lo!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3950.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Already she had grasped Nada by the hair,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3953.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he had nothing but a little stick without a knob;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3956.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet with it he rushed at the mad woman and struck her so smartly on the arm that she let go of the girl and turned on him with a yell.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3964.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Again she struck;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3966.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but he sprang into the air, and the spear passed beneath him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3969.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|A third time the woman struck,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3971.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But the weight of his body as he fell twisted it from her hand,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3975.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and before she could grasp him he was up,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3978.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the woman turned,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3979.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|drawing the spear from his wound,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_398.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|every ox in its place.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3981.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet he charged on,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3983.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and smote at her so truly that he drove the spear through her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3987.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she fell down dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3989.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which was deep,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3990.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now there were some who cried that the boy must be put to death,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3994.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because he had killed one possessed with a spirit.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_3997.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I said no, he should not be touched.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_400.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He thrust his head through the curtain of the tent and looked out.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4000.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He had killed the woman in defence of his own life and the life of his sister;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4005.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and every one had a right to slay in self-defence,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4008.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|except as against the king or those who did the king's bidding.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4012.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if the woman had a spirit,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4014.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it was an evil one,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4015.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but rather those of cattle,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4017.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the tumult grew,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4018.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|having killed one inspired,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4020.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and at last the matter came to the ears of the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4023.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he also summoned the witch-doctors.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4026.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They answered that the spirit of the dead woman would lead him to bring evil on the royal house.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_403.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The earth was white with snow,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4031.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|not on him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4032.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but on one of the royal house who should be after him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4035.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|or whether good or evil befell them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4037.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who looked him boldly in the face,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4039.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4040.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"what hast thou to say as to why thou shouldst not be killed as these men demand?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4046.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"This, Black One,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4047.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that I stabbed the woman in defence of my own life.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_405.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the air was full of it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4050.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"That is nothing,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4051.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thou shouldst then have let thyself be killed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4054.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Hast thou no other reason?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4055.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"This, Elephant,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4057.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the woman would have murdered my sister,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4059.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|whom I love better than my life.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_406.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|swept along by a cutting wind.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4061.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"That is nothing,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4062.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|If I ordered thee to be killed for any cause,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4065.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|should I not also order all within thy gates to be killed with thee?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4069.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|May not, then, a Spirit King do likewise?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4072.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|If thou hast nothing more to say thou must die.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4075.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now I grew afraid,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4076.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|not as one who pleads for his life,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4079.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but as one who demands a right:-
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_408.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now he sprang up,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4081.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have this to say,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4082.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and if it is not enough,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4083.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and let me be killed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4085.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Thou, O king, didst command that this woman should be slain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4088.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because they thought her mad.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_409.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|huddling on his clothes and as he did so calling to the Kaffirs who slept beneath the wagons.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4090.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have slain her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4091.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|whom the king commanded should be killed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4093.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I have earned not death,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4095.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let ten head of cattle be given to this boy with the heart of a man;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_41.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will answer, who know the truth.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4100.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|his father shall guard them for him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4102.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I take that which is due to me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4103.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I thank the king because he need not pay unless he will,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4107.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|As I was, so is this boy.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4110.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Only keep out of my way, for two of a kind might not agree.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4114.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for they were ill-pleased and foreboded evil.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4117.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Also they were jealous of me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4119.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But few people were killed at this feast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4122.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and many were smelt out by the witch-doctors as working magic against the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4127.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|No man might sleep safe,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4129.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as we name a finder of witches,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4131.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and led away to his death.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4133.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But when they began to work for their own ends,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4136.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and to do those to death whom he did not desire to kill,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4139.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he grew angry.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4141.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet the custom of the land was that he whom the witch-doctor touched must die,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4146.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he and all his house;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4148.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|therefore the king was in a cleft stick,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_415.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently they awoke from the stupor which already was beginning to overcome them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4151.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for he scarcely dared to save even those whom he loved.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4154.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|One night I came to doctor him, for he was sick in his mind.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4158.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and five of the bravest captains of the army had been smelt out by the Abangoma,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4164.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the witch-finders,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4165.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|together with many others.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4167.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|All had been destroyed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4169.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and men had been sent to kill the wives and children of the dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4172.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said to me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4174.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Where, then, is it to end?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4175.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Shall I myself be smelt out and slain?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4178.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|These Isanusis are too strong for me;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4181.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they lie upon the land like the shadow of night.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4184.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Tell me, how may I be free of them?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4186.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Those who walk the Bridge of Spears, O king, fall off into Nowhere,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_419.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and crept out,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4191.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered darkly;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4192.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Has not a witch-doctor a heart that can cease to beat?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4196.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Has he not blood that can be made to flow?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4198.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Thou art a bold man who darest to speak thus to me, Mopo,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4202.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4203.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I speak that which is in the king's mind,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4206.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4207.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Hearken, O king!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4208.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but what if the Isanusi be a liar?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_421.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said to them in Zulu;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4210.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|What if he smell out falsely,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4212.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bringing those to death who are innocent of evil?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4215.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Say, O king!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4216.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I leaned forward,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4218.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|whispering into the ear of the Black One,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_422.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Would you see the cattle die of the snow and wind?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4220.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he nodded heavily.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4222.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Thus I spoke then,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4223.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because I,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4224.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|saw the evil of the Isanusis,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4226.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I who knew their secrets.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4228.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I feared for my own life and for the lives of all those who were dear to me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4232.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|For they hated me as one instructed in their magic,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4236.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the king himself ran out,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4238.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|crying aloud to all people to come and see the evil that had been worked upon him by a wizard.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4243.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They came together and saw this.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4246.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the house of the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4247.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|were great smears of blood.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4249.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The knees of men strong in the battle trembled when they saw it;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_425.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they will give them some shelter.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4253.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|women wailed aloud as they wail over the dead;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4256.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Who has done this thing?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4258.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Who has dared to bewitch the king and to strike blood upon his house?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4263.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"This is no little matter,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4265.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4266.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|to be washed away with the blood of one or two and be forgotten.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_427.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And lighting a lantern he sprang out into the snow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4270.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The man who wrought it shall not die alone or travel with a few to the world of spirits.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4276.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|All his tribe shall go with him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4278.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and summon the witch-doctors from every quarter!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4281.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and there shall be such a smelling out of wizards and of witches as has not been known in Zululand!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4288.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So the messengers went out to do the bidding of the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4292.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|creeping on their knees before the majesty of the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4295.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|praised him aloud.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4296.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But he vouchsafed an answer to none.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4298.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|One noble only he caused to be killed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_43.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You did it because,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_430.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At last it was done-no easy task,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4301.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because he carried in his hand a stick of the royal red wood,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4305.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|red ivory.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4306.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the witch-doctors,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4307.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they were made hideous and terrible with the white bones of men,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4311.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with bladders of fish and of oxen,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4314.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the royal house;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4315.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|we have come from the caves and the rocks and the swamps,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4318.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|To wash in the blood of the slain;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_432.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the White Man crept back to his bed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4320.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We come not alone, O king:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4322.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with each Wise One there passes a ghost,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4324.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|red sinks the sun in the west,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4327.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We count you by hundreds, you who cried for a curse on the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4331.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|soon shall we bid you farewell!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4333.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then they were silent,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4335.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and went in silence to the place appointed for them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4338.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there to pass the night in mutterings and magic.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_434.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the shivering natives,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4341.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But those who were gathered together shivered with fear when they heard their words,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4346.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4347.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then no man might call his life his own,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4349.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The morning dawned heavily,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4351.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|their looks were sad,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4353.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they who were food for death.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4355.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They seated themselves;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4356.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then round them on the outside of the circle gathered knots of warriors,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_436.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|took refuge on the second wagon,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4360.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|great and fierce,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4362.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|When all was ready,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4363.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the king came out,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4364.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He cast one glance at the people and one at the slayers,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4368.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and wherever his eye fell men turned grey with fear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4372.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and carrying green branches in their hands.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4375.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they clapped their hands and sang softly:- We are the heralds of the king's feast.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_438.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|drawing a tent-sail over them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4381.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Vultures shall eat it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4382.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It is good-it is good to die for the king!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4385.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They ceased, and ranged themselves in a body behind us.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4389.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently from behind the royal huts appeared the great company of the Abangoma,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4394.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They were awful to see,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4395.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the bones about them rattled as they ran,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4398.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the bladders and the snake-skins floated in the air behind them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_440.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|save for the moaning of the huddled and restless cattle.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4402.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|their faces shone with the fat of anointing,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4405.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|their eyes started like the eyes of fishes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4408.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and their lips twitched hungrily as they glared round the death-ring.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4413.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|little did those evil children guess who should be the slayers and who should be the slain before that sun sank!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4420.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|On they came, like a grey company of the dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4423.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till they stood in long ranks before the Black One.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4427.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then suddenly every one of them thrust forward the little shield in his hand,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_443.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"If the snow goes on I shall lose my oxen,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4431.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with a single voice they cried,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4434.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Hail, my children!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4435.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What seekest thou, Father?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4437.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they cried again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4438.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"The blood of the guilty,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4440.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4441.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They turned and spoke each to each;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4443.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The Lion of the Zulu seeks blood.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4445.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"He shall be fed!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4447.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|screamed the women.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4448.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|screamed the women.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4449.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|His eyes search out the wizards.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_445.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said to himself;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4451.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"He shall count their dead!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4453.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|screamed the women.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4454.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Peace!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4455.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Waste not the hours in talk, but to the work.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4458.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Wizards have bewitched me!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_446.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they can never bear this cold.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4460.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Dig in the burrows of the earth and find them, ye rats!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4464.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Fly through the paths of the air and find them, ye vultures!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4468.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Smell at the gates of the people and name them, ye jackals!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4471.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Drag them from the caves if they be hidden,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4473.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|from the distance if they be fled,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4475.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|from the graves if they be dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4478.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Show them to me truly, and your gifts shall be great;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_448.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Hardly had the words passed his lips when the wagon shook;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4481.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and for them, if they be a nation, they shall be slain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4485.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Begin by companies of ten,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4487.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for you are many,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4488.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and all must be finished ere the sun sink.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4490.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4491.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then ten of the women stood forward,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4494.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who heard the voices of the dead as they cried in the night,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4497.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and spoke truly of what she heard.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4499.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|male and female,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_45.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|had it not been done,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4500.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|sat down in a half-moon facing the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4503.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but this woman drew forward,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4505.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with her came nine of her sisterhood.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4508.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then they threw themselves upon the earth and smelt it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4511.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|silence deep as midnight,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4514.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|only now and again the vultures shrieked in the trees.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4517.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Do you smell him, sisters?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4519.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"We smell him,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_452.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Once more he looked out.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4520.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4521.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4522.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Is he the son of a stranger, sisters?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4524.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He is the son of a stranger.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4526.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then they crept nearer,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4528.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|crept on their hands and knees,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_453.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|running away into the night and the snow,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4530.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till they were within ten paces of where I sat among the indunas near to the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4535.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4536.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my knees were loosened and my marrow turned to water in my bones.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4540.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|For I knew well who was that son of a stranger of whom they spoke.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4545.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was I, my father, I who was about to be smelt out;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4549.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and if I was smelt out I should be killed with all my house,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_455.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|seeking to find shelter from the cold.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4553.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the king's oath would scarcely avail me against the witch-doctors.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4558.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I looked at the fierce faces of the Isanusis before me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4561.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I say I felt like one for whom the bitterness is overpast.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4566.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and hope crept back to me like the first gleam of the dawn upon a stormy night.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4572.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for it well might happen that the king had but set a trap to catch me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4577.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now they were quite near and halted.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_458.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In a minute they had vanished utterly.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4580.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4581.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Shall I whisper his name in your ears, sisters?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4584.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They lifted their heads from the ground like snakes and nodded,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4588.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and as they nodded the necklets of bones rattled on their skinny necks.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4593.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then they drew their heads to a circle,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4595.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|we hear you!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4596.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|His is the name.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4598.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let him be named by it in the face of Heaven, him and all his house;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_46.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Perhaps it had been better to leave it, since
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_460.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There was nothing to be done, except wait for the morning.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4602.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And suddenly they sprang up and rushed towards me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4606.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and cried aloud:-
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4607.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but my tongue clave to the roof of my mouth-I could not say a word.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4612.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I glanced at the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4613.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I thought that I heard him mutter:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4615.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he held up his spear, and all was silence.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4619.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The slayers stopped in their stride,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4621.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the witch-doctors stood with outstretched arms,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4624.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the world of men was as though it had been frozen into sleep.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4627.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Hold!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4628.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Shall I be satisfied with the life of one dog?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_463.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Such search as could be made told them nothing.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4631.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Smell on, ye vultures, company by company, smell on!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4635.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So I rose, astonished, and stood on one side.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4639.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|since no such smelling out as this had been seen in the land.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4642.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Why, then, men asked in their hearts, was the death delayed?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4646.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The witch-doctors asked it also,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4648.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But from the Black One there came no word.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4651.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So we stood on one side,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4653.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|As the others had done,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4654.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so they did,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4655.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and yet they worked otherwise,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4657.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for this is the fashion of the Isanusis,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_466.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The oxen had gone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4660.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that no two of them smell out in the same way.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4663.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|naming them guilty of the witch-work.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4665.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the king to those who had been smelt out;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4668.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and ye who have hunted out their wickedness,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_467.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What was to be done?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4671.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And they named certain of the great generals,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4674.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and were in turn bidden to stand on one side together with those whom they had named.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4679.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Company by company the women doomed their victims,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_468.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he asked.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4683.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and were commanded to stand aside together with those whom they had doomed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4687.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I could see well that by this time their hearts were fearful,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_469.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|One said this thing,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4691.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for they smelt a snare.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4693.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet the king's bidding must be done,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4695.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and though their magic failed them here,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4697.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|victims must be found.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4699.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So they smelt out this man and that man till we were a great company of the doomed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_470.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but all agreed that they must wait to act until the snow melted.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4704.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who sat in silence on the ground looking at each other with sad eyes and watching the sun,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4710.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which we deemed our last,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4712.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|climb slowly down the sky.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4714.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And ever as the day waned those who were left untried of the witch-doctors grew madder and more fierce.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4721.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They leaped into the air,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4723.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and rolled upon the ground.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4724.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They drew forth snakes and devoured them alive,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4727.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they shrieked out to the spirits and called upon the names of ancient kings.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4733.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At length it drew on to evening,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4735.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the last company of the witch-doctors did their work,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4738.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the house of the women.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4740.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But there was one man of their company,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4742.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a young man and a tall,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4744.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but stood by himself in the centre of the great circle,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4747.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|fixing his eyes on the heavens.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4749.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And when this company had been ordered to stand aside also together with those whom they had smelt out,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_475.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Or till we freeze, you whose mothers were fools!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4756.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the king called aloud to the last of the witch-doctors,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4759.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|asking him of his name and tribe,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4762.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and why he alone did not do his office.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4764.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he answered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4765.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Does the king bid me to smell out him of whom the spirits have spoken to me as the worker of this deed?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4771.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4772.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|making no cries or gestures,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4775.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|saying,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4776.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I smell out the Heavens above me! "
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4778.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|A Zulu title for the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_478.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the White Man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4780.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But Chaka rose and laughed aloud.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4783.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Thou hast said it,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4784.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and thou alone!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4785.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I did the deed!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4786.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with my own hand I smote it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4788.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that I might learn who were the true doctors and who were the false!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_479.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who was in the worst of tempers,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4792.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now it seems that in the land of the Zulu there is one true doctor-this young man-and of the false,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4800.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|look at them and count them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4801.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|See!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4802.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with their wives and children,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4804.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they have doomed to the death of the dog.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4806.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now I ask you, my people, what reward shall be given to them?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_481.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He was the driver of the first wagon.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4810.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then a great roar went up from all the multitude,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4814.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Let them die, O king!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4815.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4816.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Let them die as liars should!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4818.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|men and women,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4820.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|screamed aloud in fear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4821.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and cried for mercy,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4823.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|tearing themselves with their nails,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4825.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But the king only laughed the more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4827.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said, pointing to the crowd of us who had been smelt out.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_483.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"My father,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4831.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Ye were doomed to death by these false prophets.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4834.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Slay them, my children!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4836.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|slay them all!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4837.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|stamp them out!-all!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4839.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|all, save this young man!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_484.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said to the White Man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4840.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then we bounded from the ground,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4842.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for our hearts were fierce with hate and with longing to avenge the terrors we had borne.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4848.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At last it was done, and we drew back from the heap of the dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_485.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|this is my word.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4852.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nothing was heard there now-no more cries or prayers or curses.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4857.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The witch-finders travelled the path on which they had set the feet of many.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4861.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He came alone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4862.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and all who had done his bidding bent their heads and crept past him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4867.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|praising him as they went.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4868.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and looked at the piled-up heaps of the slain and the cloud of dust that yet hung over them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_487.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The oxen are lost in the snow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4874.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"There they lie, Mopo,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4876.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which taught me to set the snare for them;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4879.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|queen of the witch-doctresses,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_488.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|No man knows whither they have gone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4881.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Well, they are dead, and the land breathes more freely;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4884.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and for the evil which they have done,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4886.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it is as yonder dust,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4888.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|something moved beneath the cloud of dust,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4891.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Slowly it forced its path,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4893.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|pushing the slain this way and that,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4895.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till at length it stood upon its feet and tottered towards us-a thing dreadful to look on.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_49.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Death chooses for himself,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_490.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|or whether they live or are now but hides and bones.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4901.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The shape was the shape of an aged woman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4904.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and even through the blood and mire I knew her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4907.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she who had doomed me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4908.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she whom but now I had smitten to earth,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4911.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but who had come back from the dead to curse me!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4915.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|On she tottered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4916.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|her apparel hanging round her in red rags,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4919.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a hundred wounds upon her face and form.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4921.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I saw that she was dying,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4923.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but life still flickered in her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4925.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she screamed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4926.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Peace, liar!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4928.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"thou art dead!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_493.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he pointed to some huts about two miles away on the hillside,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4930.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Not yet, king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4931.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|whom I would have given to the jackals,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4933.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I will not die till I have spoken.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4935.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I smelt him out this morning when I was alive;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4938.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|now that I am as one already dead, I smell him out again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4942.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|king!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4943.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And she uttered a great cry and rolled upon the ground dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4947.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"The witch lies hard and dies hard,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4949.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the king carelessly, and turned upon his heel.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4953.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There they remained like seeds in the earth,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4956.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there they grew to bring forth fruit in their season.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4960.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|after the smelling out of the witch-doctors,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4962.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and his wife Baleka,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4963.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my sister,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4964.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and report was brought to him by those who watched,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4968.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that the two women came to my huts by stealth,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_497.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the White Man.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4971.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and there kissed and nursed a boy-one of my children.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4975.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and his heart grew dark with doubt.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4977.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But to me he said nothing of the matter,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4979.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|his eyes looked over my head.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_498.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Before him was a very ancient man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4982.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He did not fear me or believe that I plotted against him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4986.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I who was his dog.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4987.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Still, he did this, though whether by chance or design I do not know:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4992.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he bade me go on a journey to a distant tribe that lived near the borders of the Amaswazi,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_4997.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there to take count of certain of the king's cattle which were in the charge of that tribe,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|his servant,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_500.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a mere bag of bones,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5002.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and to bring him account of the tale of their increase.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5005.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So I bowed before the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5007.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and said that I would run like a dog to do his bidding,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_501.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with sightless eyes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5011.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he gave me men to go with me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5013.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I returned to my huts to bid farewell to my wives and children,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5017.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and there I found that my wife,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5019.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and what came into her mind that she said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5021.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|being,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5022.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as I did not doubt,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5023.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bewitched by some enemy of my house.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5026.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I must go upon the king's business,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5028.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the mother of Nada,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_503.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and one hand-his left-white and shrivelled.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5030.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as it was thought,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5031.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I asked her why she wept thus,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5033.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who was named my son,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5035.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and whom I loved as a son,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5037.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|still in the land of life.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5038.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I tried to calm her;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5040.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the more I strove the more she wept,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5043.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|saying that she knew well that these things would be so.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5046.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now I asked her what could be done,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5048.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I was stirred by her tears,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5050.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the dread of evil crept from her to me as shadows creep from the valley to the mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5056.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She answered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5057.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|where the very skies rain blood,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5059.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"How can I do this?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_506.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|asked the old man in a thin voice.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5060.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I said.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5061.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she replied.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5062.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The king does not stand between a man and his wife.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5065.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that you love me no longer,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5066.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that I bear you no more children,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5068.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and that therefore you send me back whence I came.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5071.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5072.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and for the rest may the spirits of our fathers hold us safe.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5076.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So we kissed each other,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5078.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now at the dawning on the morrow I summoned the men whom the king had given me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_508.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet I will do it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5082.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and we started upon our journey.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5084.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|When the sun was well up we came to the banks of the river,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5088.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with her the two children.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5089.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They rose as I came,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_509.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though it is against your law,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5091.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Those with me looked at her askance.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5093.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I have divorced this woman,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5095.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I said to them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5096.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She is a withered tree,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5098.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a worn out old hag,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5099.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it is my last word.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_51.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and after all there was killing-of our own people,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5101.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What says the king?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5102.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I will answer to the king,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5103.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And we went on.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5105.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who was then a great lad drawing on to manhood,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5108.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|fierce in temper,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5109.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|well grown and broad for his years.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_511.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and you do wrong to ask me,-yes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5112.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We had journeyed seven days,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5114.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Perhaps you know the place, my father.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5116.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In it is a great and strange mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5118.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It is haunted also,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5120.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and named the Ghost Mountain,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5122.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Here in this wild place we must sleep, for darkness drew on.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5126.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now we soon learned that there were many lions in the rocks around,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5129.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for we heard their roaring and were much afraid,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5133.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who feared nothing.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5134.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So we made a circle of thorn-bushes and sat in it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5138.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently the moon came up-it was a full-grown moon and very bright,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_514.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will help you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5142.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so bright that we could see everything for a long way round.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5146.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now some six spear-throws from where we sat was a cliff,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5149.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and at the top of the cliff was a cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_515.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My father, I know what you seek.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5152.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in this cave lived two lions and their young.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5155.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|When the moon grew bright we saw the lions come out and stand upon the edge of the cliff,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5160.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with them were two little ones that played about like kittens,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5164.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that had we not been frightened it would have been beautiful to see them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5168.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I wish that I had one of the little lions for a dog.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_517.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You seek to know where your oxen have run for shelter from the cold!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5171.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The boy laughed, saying,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5173.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Then, shall I fetch you one, sister?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5175.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|No man may take young lions from their lair and live.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5178.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Such things have been done, my father,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5180.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he answered, laughing.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5181.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And no more was said of the matter.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5183.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|we saw the lioness take up the cubs in her mouth and carry them into the cave.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5188.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then she came out again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5189.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and went away with her mate to seek food,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5192.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and soon we heard them roaring in the distance.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5195.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now we stacked up the fire and went to sleep in our enclosure of thorns without fear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5201.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for we knew that the lions were far away eating game.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5204.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he did not think of the danger which he would bring upon himself and all of us.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5208.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He knew no fear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_521.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"It is so, Doctor,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5210.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|even if she thought of a thing to desire it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5212.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he slipped away to the foot of the cliff where the lions had their den.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5216.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he climbed the cliff,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5218.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|coming to the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5219.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|entered there and groped his way into it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_522.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the White Man.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5222.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The cubs heard him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5223.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thinking that it was their mother who returned,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5225.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|began to whine and purr for food.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5227.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Guided by the light of their yellow eyes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_523.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You have long ears.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5230.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|of which there were many in the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5232.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and came to where they lay.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5233.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he put out his hands and seized one of the cubs,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5237.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because he could not carry both of them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5239.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now he made haste thence before the lions returned,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5242.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and came back to the thorn fence where we lay just as dawn was breaking.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5246.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I awoke at the coming of the dawn, and, standing up, I looked out.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_525.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have long ears,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5251.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on the farther side of the thorn fence,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5253.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|looking large in the grey mist,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5255.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet dripping with blood,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5257.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Awake, my sister!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5258.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he cried;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5259.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|here is the dog you seek.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_526.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though they say that I grow deaf.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5261.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he bites now, but he will soon grow tame.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5263.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and rising,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5264.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|cried out with joy at the sight of the cub,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5267.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but for a moment I stood astonished.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5270.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I cried at last,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5271.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"let the cub go before the lions come to rend us!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5274.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I will not let it go, my father,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5276.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he answered sullenly.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5278.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Are you all afraid to meet them in the open?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_528.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have keen eyes also, and yet I cannot see your face.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5280.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"let the cub go!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5281.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But he sprang aside and avoided me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5284.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I will never let that go of which I have got hold,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5287.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"at least not living!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5289.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And suddenly he seized the head of the cub and twisted its neck;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5292.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then threw it on to the ground, and added,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5295.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|As he spoke we heard a great sound of roaring from the cave in the cliff.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5300.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The lions had returned and found one cub dead and the other gone.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5304.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We looked up.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5305.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|down the side of the cliff,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5307.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The lion ran first, and as he came he roared;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5310.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but she did not roar,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5312.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now they drew near,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5313.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|mad with fury,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5315.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Curse you for a fool, son of Mopo,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5317.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|presently I will beat you till the blood comes for this trick.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_532.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let me hearken!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5320.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"First beat the lions, then beat me if you can,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5323.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the lad,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5324.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the lions were close to us;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5326.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The lion stopped and sniffed it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5328.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he roared-ah!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5330.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he roared till the earth shook.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5333.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|As for the lioness,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5334.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and took the other into her mouth,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5336.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the lion is about to spring.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5338.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then suddenly he sprang from it like a bird,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_534.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let me look!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5341.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Catch him on the spears!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5343.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|we did the boy's bidding;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5344.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for huddling ourselves together,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5346.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But the weight of his charge carried us to the ground,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5349.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and roaring with pain and fury as he struck.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_535.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You have a farm, White Man, down near Pine Town, is it not?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5352.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently he was on his legs biting at the spears in his breast.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5356.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who alone did not wait his onslaught,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5358.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but had stepped aside for his own ends,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5361.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that with a groan the brute rolled over dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5364.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the lioness stood without the fence,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5366.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the second dead cub in her mouth,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5368.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for she could not bring herself to leave either of them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5372.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But when she heard her mate's last groan she dropped the cub and gathered herself together to spring.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5378.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She swept on towards the lad, who stood like a stone to meet her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5382.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now she met his spear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5384.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She sprang up,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5385.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the broken spear standing in her breast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5387.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5388.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as though she knew that it was he who had robbed her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_539.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you shall find your oxen-yes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5391.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and sprang with him over the fence.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5393.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Oh, save him!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5394.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|For a moment she stood over her dead cubs,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5397.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and looked at them as though she wondered;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_54.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But in those days we did not guess what we should live to see,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5400.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and we hoped that she might let him fall.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5402.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|hearing our cries,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5404.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she turned and bounded away towards the bush,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5407.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We seized our spears and followed;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5409.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|search as we would,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_541.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the little red Zulu ox with one horn,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5410.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They had vanished like a cloud.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5412.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So we came back, and, ah!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5414.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I loved the lad as though he had indeed been my son.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5418.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I knew that he was dead, and there was an end.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5421.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Where is my brother?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5422.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Lost,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5423.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5424.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Lost, never to be found again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5426.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I would that I were dead with my brother!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5428.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Let us be going,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5430.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Have you no tears to weep for your son?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5432.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|asked a man of our company.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5434.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|What is the use of weeping over the dead?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5436.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5437.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Let us be going!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5438.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The man thought these words strange,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_544.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You shall not find these, for they have died in the snow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5441.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|we waited in that place a day,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5443.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|perhaps,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5444.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the lioness would return to her den and that,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5447.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|we might kill her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5448.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But she came back no more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5450.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So on the next morning we rolled up our blankets and started forward on our journey,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5456.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nada was so weak from grief that she could hardly travel,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5460.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She buried him in her heart and said nothing.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5462.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And I too said nothing,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5464.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that the lioness of the rocks might devour him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5467.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though in public we looked sullenly on one another,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5470.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that we should never see each other's face again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5473.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|did we do so.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5474.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And I drew Nada aside and spoke to her thus:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5477.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We part, my daughter;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5478.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|nor do I know when we shall meet again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_548.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Send, and you will find the others.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5480.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the times are troubled and it is for your safety and that of your mother that I rob my eyes of the sight of you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5487.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you will soon be a woman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5488.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and you will be fairer than any woman among our people,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_549.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I ask no fee!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5491.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and it may come about that many great men will seek you in marriage,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5495.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|according to the custom of our land.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5497.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|take only a man whom you can love,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5499.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and be faithful to him alone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5500.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Here I stopped,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5502.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the girl took hold of my hand and looked into my face.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5505.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Peace, my father,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5506.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5507.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|do not speak to me of marriage,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5509.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I will wed no man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_551.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I do not work wonders for reward.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5511.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will live and die alone, and, oh!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5513.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|may I die quickly, that I may go to seek him whom I love only!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5518.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5519.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and it is not fitting that you should speak of him thus,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5521.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|even though he is dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5523.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I know nothing of such matters, my father,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5525.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she said.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5526.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I shall love him alone to the end.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5528.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you think me but a child,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_553.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the White Man scoffed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5530.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and it does not lie to me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5531.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now I upbraided the girl no more,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5534.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but one whom she might have married.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5536.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Only I marvelled that the voice of nature should speak so truly in her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5540.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|telling her that which was lawful,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5543.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|even when it seemed to be most unlawful.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5545.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5546.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for surely he is dead,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5548.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and though you cannot forget him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5549.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet speak of him no more,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_555.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But in the end, so great is the power of superstition, he sent.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5551.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that if we do not meet again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5553.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet you should keep me in your memory,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5555.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the love I bear you,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5557.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and its thorns are watered with a rain of blood,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5559.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But at last there comes an end,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5561.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and we die and go hence,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5563.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but perhaps where we go the evil may change to the good,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5567.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and those who were dear to each other on the earth may become yet dearer in the heavens;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5573.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I believe that man is not born to perish altogether,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5576.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for if these things are not so,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5578.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|at least sleep remains,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5580.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and sleep is soft,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5581.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and so farewell.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5583.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then we kissed and parted,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5585.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as they walked upon their journey to Swaziland,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5588.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and was very sad,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_559.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|those whom he sent returned with the oxen,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5590.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he who in after days was named the Slaughterer and the Woodpecker,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5595.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I must lose them also.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5597.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and did the king's business.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5599.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And on the fifth morning I rose up,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5601.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|together with those with me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5603.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who commanded us to stand.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5604.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What is it, king's men?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5606.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I asked boldly.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5607.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"This, son of Makedama,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5609.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered their spokesman:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_561.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|except the three only.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5610.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|has gone where the king's arm cannot stretch, for he is dead;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5614.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they are by now in the caves of the Swazis,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5617.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the king must seek them there with an army if he will find them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5620.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|well,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5621.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there are many girls,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5622.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet I pray him to spare her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5624.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Thus I spoke carelessly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5626.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the soldier, laughing,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5627.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Is it indeed so?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5629.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered calmly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_563.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|After that he scoffed no more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5630.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The will of the king be done.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5632.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|A cut stick puts out new leaves; I can have more children.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5636.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but first you must get new wives,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5638.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for yours are dead also,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5640.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|all five of them.
