/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5897.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now when the soldiers did not kill me I took counsel with myself,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_590.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Moreover, he had many voices, one for each of the actors in his tale.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5901.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for it was my belief that I was saved alive only that I might die later,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5906.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in a more cruel fashion.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5908.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Why should I, who was already doomed, wait to meet my doom?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5912.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|What had I left to keep me in the place of life,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5915.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|seeing that all whom I loved were dead or gone?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5918.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|To die would be easy, for I knew the ways of death.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5922.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In my girdle I carried a secret medicine;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5925.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and will never look upon the stars again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5927.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|nor would I perish more slowly beneath the knives of the tormentors,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5931.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|nor be parched by the pangs of thirst,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5934.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Therefore it was that,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5935.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|since I had sat in the doom ring looking hour after hour into the face of death,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5941.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I had borne this medicine with me by night and by day.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5945.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Surely now was the time to use it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5948.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So I thought as I sat through the watches of the night, ay!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_595.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|This man, ancient and withered, seemed to live again in the far past.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5952.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and drew out the bitter drug and laid it on my tongue.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5955.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But as I did so I remembered my daughter Nada,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5958.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who was left to me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5960.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though she sojourned in a far country,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5962.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who still lived,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5963.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so said the soldiers,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5965.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though how it came about that the king had not killed her I did not know then.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5970.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Also another thought was born in my heart.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5973.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I might be revenged upon him who had wrought me this woe;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5977.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but can the dead strike?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5979.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the dead are strengthless,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5980.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and if they still have hearts to suffer,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5983.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they have no hands to give back blow for blow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5986.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nay, I would live on.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5987.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Time to die when death could no more be put away.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_599.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was the past that spoke to his listener,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5991.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Death chooses for himself and answers no questions;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5994.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he is a guest to whom none need open the door of his hut,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_5998.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Not yet would I taste of that medicine of mine.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who slew him with the Princes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_60.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as it was heard in life so it shall be heard in story,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6001.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the sun had sunk as we passed through the gates.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6004.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as he had been commanded,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6006.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the captain of those who watched me went in before the king and told him that I lay without in bonds.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6012.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And the king said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6013.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let him be brought before me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6015.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who was my physician,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6016.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that I may tell him how I have doctored those of his house.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_602.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|telling of deeds long forgotten,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6021.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and pushed me through the doorway of the great hut.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6024.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now a fire burned in the hut,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6026.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the night was cold,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6027.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|looking towards the opening of the hut,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6030.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the smoke from the fire wreathed him round,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6033.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and its light shone upon his face and flickered in his terrible eyes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6038.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I broke from them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6039.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and prostrating myself,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_604.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|of deeds that are no more known.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6041.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for my arms were free,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6043.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the councillors bowed themselves on either side,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6046.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and laid their hands on their sticks,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6048.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|their foreheads touching the ground.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6050.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I sat down on the floor of the hut over against the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6055.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and we talked through the fire.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6057.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Tell me of the cattle that I sent thee to number,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6059.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|son of Makedama,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_606.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet as he best may,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6061.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said Chaka.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6062.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6063.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|forgetting none.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6064.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So I sat and told him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6066.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and heifer by heifer,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6067.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|forgetting none;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6068.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I knew that he did not sleep,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_607.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in many ways,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6071.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for all the while the firelight flickered in his fierce eyes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6075.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he would learn of the cattle before he killed me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6077.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At length all the tale was told.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_608.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he has done more,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6080.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6081.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it goes well.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6082.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There are yet honest men left in the land.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6085.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that sorrow has come upon thy house while thou wast about my business.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6089.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered, as one who speaks of a small matter.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6092.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|sorrow has come upon thy house,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6094.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that the fire from above ran briskly through thy huts.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6098.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and dreaming there was no escape,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_610.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he has printed it that others may judge of it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6100.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Thou hast heard these things, Mopo, but thou hast not yet heard all.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6105.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6106.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|acted wisely,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6107.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and wailed aloud as though in utter grief.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6109.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Spare my ears, Black One!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6112.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Tell me not that she who bore thee is dead, O Lion of the Zulu.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6116.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|For the others, what is it?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6117.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It is a breath of wind, it is a drop of water;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_612.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And now his part is played.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6120.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but this trouble is as the gale or as the sea.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6123.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Cease, my servant, cease!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6125.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thou hast done well to grieve aloud,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6128.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because the Mother of the Heavens is no more,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6130.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|For hadst thou done this last thing or left the first undone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6134.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I should have known that thy heart was wicked,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6137.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It is well for thee, then, that thou hast read my riddle aright.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_614.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but who had another name,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6141.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but it was not to be, for this was but the beginning of my trial.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6145.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6146.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|These were her words:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6148.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and thy wives,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6149.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|had conspired together to give a child to me who would be childless.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6154.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|These were her words,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6155.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the words that came to me through the singing of the fire.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6158.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the girl who is named Nada?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_616.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|take up the story.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6160.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6161.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said Chaka.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6162.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|enough of her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6163.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|surely the Mother of the Heavens was maddened by the Heavens when she sang that song,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6168.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6169.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I know nothing of it, O king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_617.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the most beautiful of Zulu women.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6171.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6172.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And again he looked at me terribly through the reek of the fire.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6176.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Surely thou art a-cold; thy hands shake with cold.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6180.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nay, man, fear not-warm them, warm them, Mopo.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6184.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|See, now, plunge that hand of thine into the heart of the flame!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6188.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|to where the fire glowed reddest-ay,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_619.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but you are here for many nights,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6191.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he pointed and laughed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6193.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I grew cold indeed-yes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6195.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I grew cold who soon should be hot,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6198.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He would put me to the trial by fire.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6201.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the king spoke again in a great voice:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6204.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nay, Mopo, be not so backward;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6206.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|shall I sit warm and see thee suffer cold?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_621.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it shall be told.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6210.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|take the hand of Mopo,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6211.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and hold it to the flame,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6213.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that his heart may rejoice in the warmth of the flame while we speak together of this matter of the child that was,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_622.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I have much to say that is sorrowful,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6220.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so my mother sang,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6221.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"There is little need for that, O king,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6223.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|being made bold by fear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6225.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I saw that if I did nothing death would swiftly end my doubts.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6230.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I bethought me of the poison that I bore,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6232.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and was minded to swallow it and make an end,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6235.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the desire to live is great,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6237.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so I said to my heart,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6239.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will endure this also;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6241.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|afterwards, if need be, I can die.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6244.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Speak on, O king, while I warm myself, and thou shalt hear true words,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6248.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I said boldly.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_625.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Do you know who I am, my father?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6250.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6251.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I stretched out my left hand and plunged it into the fire-not into the hottest of the fire,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6257.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but where the smoke leapt from the flame.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6260.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now my flesh was wet with the sweat of fear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6263.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I knew that the torment was to come.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6265.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he spoke slowly, that the fire might find time to do its work.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_627.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You do not know.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6270.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I know this only, O king!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6272.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that I killed the child in obedience to thy word,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6275.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and laid its body before thee.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6277.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6278.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the steam from my flesh had been drawn from my hand by the heat,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_628.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So men have thought for many years, but that is not my name.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6283.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the flame got hold of me and ate into my flesh,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6287.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But of this I showed no sign upon my face,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6290.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6291.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|having failed in the trial,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6293.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|death would be my portion.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6294.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the king spoke again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6296.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Dost thou swear by my head,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6298.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I swear it by thy head,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6300.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6301.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And now, my father, the agony of the fire was such as may not be told.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6307.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I felt my eyes start forward in their sockets,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6310.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my blood seemed to boil within me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6313.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it rushed into my head,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6315.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and down my face there ran two tears of blood.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6318.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But yet I held my hand in the fire and made no sign,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_632.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Few have known it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6323.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and that moment seemed to me as all the years of my life.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6327.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said at length,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6328.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Withdraw thy hand from the flame.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6330.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I am answered;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6332.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thou hast passed the trial;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6333.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thy heart is clean;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6335.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"It is well, O king,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6336.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I said calmly.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6338.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But as I spoke I looked at my left hand.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_634.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I have kept it locked in my breast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6341.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was black,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6342.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father-black as a charred stick,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6346.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the nails were gone from the twisted fingers.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6349.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Look at it now, my father; you can see, though my eyes are blind.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6354.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The hand is white, like yours-it is white and dead and shrivelled.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6359.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have had but little use of that hand since this night of torment.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_636.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Look at this hand, my father-no, not that which is withered with fire;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6364.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I used it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6365.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for in such a matter my oath had not helped thee.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6368.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in this there is witchcraft.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6370.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|such a mourning as has not been seen in Zululand,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6374.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for all the people on the earth shall weep at it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6377.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But we will summon no witch-doctors,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6379.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thou and I will be witch-doctors,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6382.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and ourselves shall smell out those who have brought these woes upon us.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6386.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|shall my mother die unavenged,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6389.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she who bore me and has perished by witchcraft,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6392.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my faithful servant,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6394.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|whom I have honoured with the warmth of my fire,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6397.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|go forth!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6398.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And once again he stared at me through the reek of the flame,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_64.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|however humbly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6402.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I praised the king with a loud voice,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6405.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the house of the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6406.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I walked slowly through the gates,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6409.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but when I was without the gates the anguish that took me because of my burnt hand was more than I could bear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_641.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You see it, though I who am blind cannot.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6416.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There I found fat,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6418.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and having plunged my hand in the fat,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6420.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I wrapped it round with a skin and passed out again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6424.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I could not stay still.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6426.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I went to and fro,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6427.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till at length I reached the spot where my huts had been.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_643.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But still, within me, I see it as it was once.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6431.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The outer fence of the huts still stood; the fire had not caught it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6436.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I passed through the fence;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6437.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there within were the ashes of the burnt huts-they lay ankle-deep.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6442.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I walked in among the ashes;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6444.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my feet struck upon things that were sharp.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6447.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The moon was bright, and I looked;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6449.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they were the blackened bones of my wives and children.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6452.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I flung myself down in the ashes in bitterness of heart;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6456.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there I lay,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6457.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and on me were the ashes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6459.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and among the ashes were the bones.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_646.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I see it red and strong-red with the blood of two kings.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6461.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yes, not to me alone, but to many another also.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6465.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I lay among the ashes and groaned with the pain of my burn,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6469.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and groaned also from the desolation of my heart.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6473.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Why did I not taste it now and make an end?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6475.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I would not give him this last triumph over me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6479.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|having passed the fire,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6480.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|once more I should be great in the land,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6483.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I would become great.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6484.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and become great,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6486.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that in a day to be I might wreak vengeance on the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6490.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6491.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|to the ghosts of my ancestors.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6493.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the great soul of the world,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6495.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who moves through the heavens and the earth unseen and unheard.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6499.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And thus I prayed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_65.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|mine may pass down with it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_650.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Listen, my father; bend your ear to me and listen.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6501.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And while I prayed I slept,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6503.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if I did not sleep,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6504.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the light of thought went out of me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6507.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I became as one dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6509.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then there came a vision to me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6511.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a vision that was sent in answer to my prayer,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6514.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it was a madness born of my sorrows.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6516.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it seemed to me that I stood upon the bank of a great and wide river.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6521.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was gloomy there,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6522.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the light lay low upon the face of the river,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6525.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but far away on the farther side was a glow like the glow of a stormy dawn,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6530.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and out of the reeds came men and women and children,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6533.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|by hundreds and thousands,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6535.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and plunged into the waters of the river and were buffeted about by them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_654.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I felt you start;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6540.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|all the people that I saw in the water were black people,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6544.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And I saw the countless faces of those in the water,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6547.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|among them were many that I knew.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6549.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and near him was my own face;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_655.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he died on the Ghost Mountain;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6551.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the prince,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6552.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|his brother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6553.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but only lost.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6555.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I saw that behind the bank was a cliff,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6558.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|mighty and black,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6559.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in the cliff were doors of ivory,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6562.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and through them came light and the sound of laughter;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6565.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there were other doors also,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6567.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|black as though fashioned of coal,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6569.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and on the seat was the figure of a glorious woman.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_657.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I also was on the Ghost Mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6572.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She was tall,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6573.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she alone was white,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6575.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and clad in robes of white,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6577.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and her hair was like gold which is molten in the fire,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6581.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and her face shone like the midday sun.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6584.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I saw that those who came up out of the river stood before the woman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6589.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the water yet running from them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_659.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In those days my feet still could travel fast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6591.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and cried aloud to her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6592.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the figure of the glorious woman held a rod in either hand,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6596.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the rod in her right hand was white and of ivory,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6600.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And as those who came up before her throne greeted her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6604.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and now with the wand of ebony in her left hand.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6607.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|through which came light and laughter,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6609.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with the wand of ebony she pointed to the gates of coal,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6614.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|through which came blackness and groans.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6617.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And as she pointed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6618.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|some through the gates of light and some through the gates of blackness.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6623.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as I stood,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6624.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a handful of people came up from the bank of the river.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6627.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I looked on them and knew them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6629.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and all my other wives and children,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_663.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I travelled by day, and by night I found him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6631.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and those who had perished with them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6633.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They stood before the figure of the woman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6636.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the Princess of the Heavens,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6637.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and cried aloud,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6639.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|pointed with the rod of ivory to the gates of ivory;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6642.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but still they stood before her, not moving.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6646.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|in a low voice that was sad and awful to hear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6649.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Why tarry ye?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6650.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Pass in through the gates of light.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6653.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who on earth was named Mother of the Heavens,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6655.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on behalf of all this company,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6657.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for justice on him who murdered us.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_666.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Why do I tell you this?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6660.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"How is he named?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6661.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the voice of Unandi.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6663.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Many have come to ask for vengeance on that head,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6666.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the voice of the Queen of the Heavens,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6668.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and many more shall come.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_667.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will tell you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6670.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it shall fall,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6671.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|With the spear that pierced thy breast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6674.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|ye wives and children of Mopo,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6676.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the hand that pierces shall be the hand of Mopo.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6679.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|As I guide him so shall he go.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_668.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and because he had murdered my wives and children.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6681.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Ay, I will teach him to wreak my vengeance on the earth!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6685.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Thus I dreamed, my father.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6687.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but that was on the earth and with my waking eyes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6691.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and did I weave these visions from the woof of my madness?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6695.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it was the pain of my burnt hand that aroused me from my sleep or from my stupor.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_67.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I must leave the ways of action that I love and bury myself in books,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6700.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I rose shaking the ashes from me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6703.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|waiting till the king's women,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6705.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At last they came,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6706.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently I saw her;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6708.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then she came up to me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6709.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and we greeted one another,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6711.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|gazing heavily into each other's eyes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6713.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|See now what has sprung from this seed!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6715.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I held out my withered hand towards her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6718.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Ay, Mopo, my brother,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_672.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There are great names in the story, my father.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6721.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she answered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6722.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but flesh is nearest to flesh,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6724.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as I have heard but now.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6726.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|have lost-all I love?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6728.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but for me there is no hope,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6729.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the king looks on me no more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6732.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I grieve for you,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6733.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I had this one alone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6735.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Think you that I shall escape?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6736.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I tell you nay.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6737.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I am but spared for a little, then I go where the others have gone.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_674.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yes, many have heard the names:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6742.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for a little while I may be left, then I die:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6745.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I care not, I am weary, but I grieve for the boy;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6749.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there was no such boy in the land.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6751.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Would that I might die swiftly and go to seek him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6754.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"And if the boy is not dead, Baleka, what then?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6757.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What is that you said?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6758.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she answered, turning on me with wild eyes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6761.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But last night I dreamed a dream,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6763.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I told her all my dream,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6766.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and also of that which had gone before the dream.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6769.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she said at length.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_677.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have felt the mountains shake and seen the waters quiver in their sound.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6770.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You were ever a strange man, to whom the gates of distance are no bar.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6774.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and now I shall die happy.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6776.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yes, gainsay me not; I shall die, I know it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6780.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I read it in the king's eyes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6782.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But what is it?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6783.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Your love is great, woman,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6784.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and it may well happen that in the end it shall all be for nothing,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6788.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Say now, what shall I do?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6790.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Shall I fly, or shall I abide here, taking the chance of things?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6794.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|See, now!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6795.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|This is in the king's mind.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6796.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he is afraid lest the people should turn upon him who killed his own mother.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6801.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Therefore he will give it out that he did not kill her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6804.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|As he said to you,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6805.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there will be a smelling out,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6807.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but a smelling out of a new sort,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6809.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and at that smelling out he will give to death all those whom he fears,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_681.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But where are they now?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6814.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as he shall say,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6815.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and did not your wives and children also perish by witchcraft?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6819.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Therefore, do not fly;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_682.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I opened the gates of distance for the holders of the names.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6820.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|abide here and become great-become great to the great end of vengeance,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6825.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|soon you will have more,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6826.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6827.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and my blood also shall cry for vengeance to you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6830.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Are there not other princes in the land?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6832.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|what of Umpanda,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6834.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|brothers to the king?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6835.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Do not these also desire to be kings?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6837.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Do they not day by day rise from sleep feeling their limbs to know if they yet live,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6843.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Draw near to them, my brother;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6845.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|creep into their hearts and learn their counsel or teach them yours;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6849.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and where I also am about to tread.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6851.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|leaving me pondering,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6853.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for her words were heavy with wisdom.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6855.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I knew well that the brothers of the king went heavily and in fear of death,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_686.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They passed through and they are gone beyond.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6860.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|little could be done,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6861.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for he lived softly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6863.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|speaking always as one whose wits are few.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6866.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and as I was doctoring it there came a messenger to me summoning me before the king.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6871.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|calling him by his royal names;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6873.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but he took me by the hand and raised me up, speaking softly.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6877.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6878.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Thou hast suffered much woe because of the witchcraft of thine enemies.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_688.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I cut the strings that tied them to the world.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6882.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have lost my mother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6884.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thou hast lost thy wives and children.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6886.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because I have lost my mother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6888.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|by the witchcraft of our foes!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6890.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the king, when the weeping was done.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6893.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|None can give me back my mother;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6895.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I can give thee more wives, and thou shalt find children.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6900.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Go in among the damsels who are reserved to the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6903.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|go in among the cattle of the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6905.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and choose thee ten times ten of the best;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6908.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|On the first day of the new moon I summon a great meeting,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_691.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They fell off!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6912.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then we will mourn together over our woes;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6915.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then, too, we will learn who brought these woes upon us.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6919.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Go now, Mopo, go!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_692.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Perhaps they are falling still,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6920.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|leaving me to weep alone because my mother is dead!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6924.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6925.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I grew greater in the land than ever I had been before.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6929.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I chose the cattle, they were fat;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6931.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I chose the wives, they were fair;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6934.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I took no pleasure in them, nor were any more children born to me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6939.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|For my heart was like a withered stick;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_694.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I wish I knew the snakes that I might crush them with my heel.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6942.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and lost in my sorrow for those whom I had loved.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6945.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6946.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will go back a little,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6948.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as he told it to me in the after years.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6950.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Once he struggled,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6952.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but she bit him hard,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6953.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so he lay quiet in her mouth,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6955.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and looking back he saw the face of Nada as she ran from the fence of thorns,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6961.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|crying
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6962.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Save him!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6963.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he heard her words,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6964.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then he saw and heard little more,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6966.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|into a deep sleep.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6968.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|feeling pain in his thigh,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6970.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|where the lioness had bitten him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6972.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and heard a sound of shouting.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6974.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He looked up;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6975.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|near to him stood the lioness that had loosed him from her jaws.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6979.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She was snorting with rage,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_698.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yonder, beneath us, at the burying-place of kings, there is a hole.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6981.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in front of her was a lad long and strong,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6985.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with a grim face,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6986.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|black and grey,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6987.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bound about his shoulders in such fashion that the upper jaw and teeth of the wolf rested on his head.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6994.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in one hand he held a large war-shield,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_6997.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in the other he grasped a heavy club shod with iron.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7001.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the lioness crouched herself to spring,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7004.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the lad with the club did not wait for her onset.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7007.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He ran in upon her and struck her on the head with the club.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7011.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but this did not kill her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7012.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He caught the blow upon his shield,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7015.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the shield was driven against his breast so strongly that he fell backwards beneath it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_702.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Far away in Zululand there is a cleft upon the Ghost Mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7021.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and lay there howling like a wolf in pain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7024.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the lioness sprang upon him and worried him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7027.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because of the shield,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7028.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as yet she could not come at him to slay him;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7031.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and its blade was a span deep in her breast.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7035.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that he would drive the spear home or die.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7038.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So he rose swiftly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7039.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for strength came back to him in his need,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7042.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and ran to where the lioness worried at him who lay beneath the shield.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7046.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She did not heed him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7048.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so he flung himself upon his knees before her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7051.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|seizing the haft of the broken spear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7054.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|drove it deep into her and wrenched it round.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7057.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and clawed at him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7059.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then, as he lay, he heard a mighty howling, and, behold!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_706.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the king who died for Nada.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7063.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the light went out of his eyes so that he was as one dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7068.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At length his mind came back to him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7070.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he remembered the lioness and looked up to find her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7073.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But he did not find her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7075.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|while all about him were the skins of beasts,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7078.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and at his side was a pot filled with water.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_708.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was far to fall and he was heavy;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7081.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|taking the pot,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7082.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|drank of the water,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7084.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and then he saw that his arm was wasted as with sickness,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7088.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and that his breast was thick with scars scarcely skinned over.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7092.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now while he lay and wondered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7094.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the mouth of the cave was darkened,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7096.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bearing a dead buck upon his shoulders.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7099.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|looked at him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_71.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the old days and friends are in my mind,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7100.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"your eyes are open-do you, then, live, stranger?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7103.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I am hungry.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7104.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the other,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7105.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|since with toil I bore you here through the forest,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7108.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for twelve days you have lain without sense,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_711.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|those bones of his are broken into little pieces.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7111.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|drinking water only.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7112.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So deeply had the lion clawed you that I thought of you as dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7116.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that you might cease to suffer and I to be troubled;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7119.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I held my hand,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7120.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because of a word which came to me from one who is dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7124.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now eat, that your strength may return to you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7127.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Afterwards, we will talk.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7128.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and little by little his health returned to him-every day a little.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7133.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as they sat at night by the fire in the cave they spoke together.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7137.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"How are you named?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7138.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I am named Galazi the Wolf,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7140.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he answered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7141.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|was my great-grandfather.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7143.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Whence came you, Galazi?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7144.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which I should rule.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7146.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|This is the story:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7147.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the end of it was that he killed the chief of the tribe and took his place.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_715.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I went to see them when the vultures and the jackals had done their work.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7151.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|After he was dead, my father ruled in his place;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7154.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but there was a great party in the tribe that hated his rule because he was of the Zulu race,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7159.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for my father's hand was heavy on the people.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7161.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now I was the only son of my father by his head wife,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7165.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and therefore those of the Swazi party,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7167.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they were many and great,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7169.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|hated me also.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7170.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So matters stood till last year in the winter,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7173.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with their wives and children,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7175.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because he knew that they plotted against him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7177.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So she poisoned him in the night and in the morning it was told me that my father lay sick and summoned me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_718.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And then I laughed three times and came here to die.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7183.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I went to him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7184.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she stands yonder who has done the deed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7187.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|her chin upon her breast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7189.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|trembling as she looked upon the fruit of her wickedness.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7192.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the girl was young and fair,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7194.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and we had been friends,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7195.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet I say that I did not pause,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7197.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I did not pause,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7198.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|seizing my spear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7199.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I killed her with the spear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7201.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But if they drive you out and you still live,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7204.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|swear this to me-that you will not rest till you have avenged me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7208.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|every one of them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7209.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|except those of my own blood,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7211.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|This I know of you now in my hour of death:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7213.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|child of Siguyana,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7215.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and wandering in another land you shall die a man's death,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7219.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and not such a death as yonder witch has given to me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_722.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|All that is long ago, and I have not died;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7222.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|having spoken thus,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7223.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he lifted up his head,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7224.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with a great groan he died.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7226.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now I passed out of the hut dragging the body of the dead girl after me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7231.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I saw that their looks were sullen.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7233.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who am the chief,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7234.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he who had persuaded her to the deed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7237.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he was maddened at the sight.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7239.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The old lion is dead,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7240.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|shaking their spears.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7241.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I did not hasten,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7243.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I knew well that I should not die then,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7245.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I knew it from my father's last words.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7247.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I waited till the man was near me;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7249.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he thrust,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_725.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that you may repeat it to the white men if you will.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7250.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I sprang aside and drove my spear through him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7253.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and on the daughter's body the father fell dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7256.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I shouted aloud and rushed through them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7259.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|None touched me;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7260.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|none could catch me;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7261.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the man does not live who can overtake me when my feet are on the ground and I am away.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7266.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Yet I might try,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7268.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for of all lads among the Zulus he was the swiftest of foot.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7272.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"First walk again, then run,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7274.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered Galazi.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7275.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it is a merry one.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7276.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Something is left to tell, stranger.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7278.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|nor did I linger at all in the land of the Swazis,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_728.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nay, I do not know.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7281.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but came on swiftly into the Zulu.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7284.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But while I journeyed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7285.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|finding food and shelter as I might,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7287.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and to him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7288.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|when I had stayed there two days,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_729.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Very, very old.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7290.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I told my tale.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7292.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But the old man counselled me against my plan,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7294.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and would kill me;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7295.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and thought no more of standing before the king to cry for justice,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7299.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for he who cries to kings for justice sometimes finds death.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_730.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We were not a large tribe;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7303.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for he had sons to come after him who looked on me with no liking;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7308.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|not knowing where I should go.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7309.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you are tall and strong and swift of foot.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7312.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Would you earn a famous weapon,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7314.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and asked what I should do to win it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7316.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You shall climb the path and enter a gloomy forest.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_732.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|perhaps there were between two and three thousand of them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7320.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It is very dark in the forest,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7322.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but you must push through it till you come to an open place with a wall of rock behind it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7327.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In the wall of rock is a cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7329.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in the cave you will find the bones of a man.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7332.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Bring down the bones in a bag,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7334.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Do not heed her: she is crazy.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7336.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The mountain is haunted; it is a place of ghosts.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7339.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Look at the stone Witch who sits upon it!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7341.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Evil spirits live in that forest,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7343.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and no man has walked there for many years.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7346.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|This woman's son was foolish:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7348.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he went to wander in the forest,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_735.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but they were brave.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7350.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|saying that he cared nothing for ghosts,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7352.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the ghost-folk,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7353.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|That was many years ago, and none have dared to seek his bones.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7356.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|offering the great club for a reward;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7359.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The ghosts live only in their cowardly hearts; there are but wolves.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7363.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I know that the bones of my son lie in the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7367.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I have seen them in a dream;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7368.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my old limbs are too weak to carry me up the mountain path,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_737.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now they are all dead,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7372.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and all these are cowards;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7374.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there is no man among them since the Zulus killed my husband,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7378.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answering nothing;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7379.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but when all had done,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_738.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and their women and children with them,-that people is no more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7380.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the spirits who lived in the forest upon the Ghost Mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7384.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the old woman rose, and creeping on her hands went into the hut.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7388.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently she returned again, dragging the great club after her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7392.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Was there ever such a club?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7394.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that was a club,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7395.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|black as iron that had been smoked in the fire,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7398.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and shod with metal that was worn smooth with smiting.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_74.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|nor while I have memory shall I forget them and you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7402.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a great desire came into my heart to possess it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7405.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Five men have held that club in war and a hundred-and-seventy-three have given up their lives beneath its strokes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7413.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He who held it last slew twenty before he was slain himself,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7418.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for this fortune goes with the club-that he who owns it shall die holding it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_742.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It is gone like last month's moon;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7424.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but in a noble fashion.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7426.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Watcher of the Fords,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7427.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|side by side,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7429.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he who owns it smites great blows indeed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7432.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|None dare own the Watcher of the Fords.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7434.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And pondered a time,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7436.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At length she rose,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7437.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I must seek me a man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7439.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I should see little of you again or of the good club either.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_744.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Our tribe lived in a beautiful open country;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7443.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but if I live I will bring you back the bones,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7446.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if I do not find them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7447.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will render the Watcher into your hands again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7450.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At the least I say that if you will not lend me the club,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7453.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|If you die, let the club be lost with you;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7456.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if you fail, bring it back to me;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7459.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then it is yours,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7460.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and it shall bring you glory and you shall die a man's death at last holding him aloft among the dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7468.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and made ready to start.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7469.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The old woman blessed me and bade me farewell,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_747.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|standing as high as a man's elbow only,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7472.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|praying me not to go,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7474.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the forest on the Ghost Mountain had an evil name:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7477.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who howled like wolves.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7479.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I thanked the girl,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7480.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but to the others I said nothing,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7482.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now stranger,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7483.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if you have strength,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7484.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|come to the mouth of the cave and look out,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7486.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the moon is bright.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7488.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|shaped like a seated woman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_749.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My mother was very fond of these cows,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7490.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|her chin resting upon her breast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7492.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on the lap of the woman.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7494.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Below this place the rock sloped sharply,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7497.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and was clothed with little bushes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7500.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Lower down yet was a forest,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7502.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|great and dense,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7503.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that stretched to the top of a cliff,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7505.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and at the foot of the cliff,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7507.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|beyond the waters of the river,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7509.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Yonder, stranger,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7510.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|pointing with the club Watcher of the Fords far away to the plain beneath;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7515.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the people of the ghosts;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7517.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on the hither side of the forest,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7518.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|runs the path to the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_752.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and there was one with a white face that would follow her about.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7520.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and here is the cave itself.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7522.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|See this stone lying at the mouth of the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7524.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it turns thus,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7526.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|shutting up the entrance hole-it turns gently;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7530.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though it is so large,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7531.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a child may move it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7532.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for it rests upon a sharp point of rock.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7535.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he pointed to a mark in the mouth of the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7538.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then that man need be strong who can draw it back again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7541.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though I have done it myself,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7543.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who am not a man full grown.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7545.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it will roll down the neck of the cave like a pebble down the neck of a gourd,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7549.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|one striving from within and one dragging from without,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_755.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the boys went on with the cattle,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7553.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Look now, I close the stone, as is my custom of a night, so,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7557.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he grasped the rock and swung it round upon its pivot,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7561.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on which it turned as a door turns.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7563.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and though,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7564.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|none would guess that a cave was here,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7566.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But enough of the stone.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7568.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I will go forward with my tale,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_757.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My mother sat down on the grass and nursed her baby,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7570.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was in flood, and few had dared to cross it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7573.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|watch by the ford you who would win the Watcher of the Ford!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7576.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Beat the water with the club,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7578.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|only I bound the shield upon my shoulders with a string,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7581.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the bag that I had brought I made fast about my middle,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7585.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I held the great club in my teeth by the thong.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7588.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and those on the bank shouted that I was lost;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7591.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I rose again, and in the end I won the farther shore.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7595.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now those on the bank mocked no more;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7597.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they stood still wondering,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7599.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I walked on till I came to the foot of the cliff.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_760.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the cow grazed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7602.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|That cliff is hard to climb, stranger;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7605.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|when you are strong upon your feet, I will show you the path.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7608.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet I found a way up it, and by midday I came to the forest.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_761.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She walked like one who is tired.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7612.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and ate a little food that I had brought with me in the bag,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7615.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if ghosts there were.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7616.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I rose and plunged into the forest.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7619.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and their leaves are so thick that in certain places the light is as that of night when the moon is young.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7625.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Still, I wended on, often losing my path.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7628.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and shaped my course towards her knees.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_763.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|On her back was a bundle of mats,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7631.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and ever I looked round searching for the eyes of the Amatongo.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7635.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I saw no spirits,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7637.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though at times great spotted snakes crept from before my feet,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7641.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and perhaps these were the Amatongo.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7644.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and always high above my head the wind sighed in the great boughs with a sound like the sighing of women.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_765.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she led by the hand a boy of about my own age,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7650.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|singing to myself as I went,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7652.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and at length,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7653.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|towards the end of the second hour,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7655.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the trees grew fewer,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7657.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the ground sloped upwards,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7659.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But, stranger, you are weary, and the night wears on;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7662.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|sleep now, and to-morrow I will end the tale.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7665.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Say, first, how are you named?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7667.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he answered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7668.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"and my tale shall be told when yours is done; let us sleep!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7672.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now when Galazi heard this name he started and was troubled,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7677.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but said nothing.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7678.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So they laid them down to sleep,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7680.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|all that day he rested in the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7683.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In the evening he returned,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7684.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I had passed the forest,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7686.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Here the sun shone merrily,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7688.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|here lizards ran and birds flew to and fro,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_769.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but bigger and stronger than I was.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7691.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So I climbed up the steep rock,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7693.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|where little bushes grow like hair on the arms of a man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7696.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which are the space before the cave.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7698.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I lifted my head over the brink of the rock and looked,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_77.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Elephant that is not turned!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7701.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my blood ran cold and my heart turned to water,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7704.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|before the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7706.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|many and great.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7707.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Some slept and growled in their sleep,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7709.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|some gnawed at the skulls of dead game,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_771.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We waited a long while,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7712.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|some sat up like dogs and their tongues hung from their grinning jaws.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7716.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and beyond I discovered the mouth of the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7719.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|where the bones of the boy should be.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_772.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for she was very weary.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7721.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I had no wish to come there,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7723.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|being afraid of the wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7724.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|even as I turned,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7726.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now whether this was by chance or whether the Watcher would shame him who bore it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7730.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I do not know.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7731.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At the least, shame entered into me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7734.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And if I wished to go,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7735.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|should I not be killed by the ghosts at night in the forest?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7739.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nay, it was better to die in the jaws of the wolves, and at once.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_774.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We saw by the way her hair was dressed that she was not of our tribe.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7743.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Thus I thought in my heart;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7744.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7745.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|tarrying not,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7746.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|lest fear should come upon me again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7748.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I swung up the Watcher,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7750.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|sprang up and stood howling,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7751.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with bristling hides and fiery eyes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7754.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the smell of them came into my nostrils.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7756.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet when they saw it was a man that rushed upon them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7759.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they were seized with sudden fear and fled this way and that,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7763.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|leaping by great bounds from the place of rock,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7766.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that presently I stood alone in front of the cave.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7769.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|having conquered the wolf ghosts and no blow struck,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7772.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my heart swelled within me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7774.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I walked to the mouth of the cave proudly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7777.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as a cock walks upon a roof,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7779.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and looked in through the opening.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_778.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the woman.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7781.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|As it chanced,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7782.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the sinking sun shone at this hour full into the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7785.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that all its darkness was made red with light.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7788.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I grew afraid indeed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_779.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered my mother.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7790.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I could see the end of the cave.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7792.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Look now!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7793.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There is a hole in the wall of the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7795.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|twice the height of a man from the floor.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7797.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and a man might sit in it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7799.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|his legs hanging towards the floor of the cave.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_780.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Food, and a hut to sleep in,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7801.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And there a man sat, or that which had been a man.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7805.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There sat the bones of a man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7807.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the black skin had withered on his bones,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7810.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|holding them together,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7811.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and making him awful to see.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7813.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|His hands were open beside him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7815.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he leaned upon them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7816.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|His eyes also were bound round with a band of leather,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_782.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the woman.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7820.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as though to hide something from their gaze,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7822.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|one foot was gone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7823.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|one hung over the edge of the niche towards the floor,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7826.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and beneath it on the floor,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7828.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|red with rust,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7829.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|lay the blade of a broken spear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_783.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have travelled far.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7832.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now come hither,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7833.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|place your hand upon the wall of the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7835.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|is it not?-smooth as the stones on which women grind their corn.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7839.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will tell you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_784.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"How are you named?-and what is your people?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7840.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|When I peered through the door of the cave I saw this:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7843.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on the floor of the cave lay a she-wolf panting,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7846.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as though she had galloped many a mile;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7848.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she was great and fierce.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7850.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Near to her was another wolf-he was a dog-old and black,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7854.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bigger than any I have seen,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7855.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a very father of wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7857.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But this wolf was on his feet.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7859.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|As I watched he drew back nearly to the mouth of the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7863.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and there for a second he seemed to cling,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7865.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|while his great jaws closed with a clash but a spear's breadth beneath the dead man's foot.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_787.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|asked my mother.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7871.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he fell back with a howl of rage, and drew slowly down the cave.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7875.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Again he ran and leaped,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7877.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|again the great jaws closed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7879.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|again he fell down howling.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_788.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the stranger.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7881.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they sprang together,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7883.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But it was all in vain;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7884.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|seeking to devour the bones of him who sat above.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7887.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but never might their clashing jaws close upon his foot.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_789.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now there had been war between our people and the Zulu people,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7891.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|One foot they had, indeed, but the other they could not come by.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7895.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now as I watched,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7896.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|filled with fear and wonder,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7898.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the she-wolf,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7899.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|her tongue lolling from her jaws,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_79.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You who nursed us from of old!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7901.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|made so mighty a bound that she almost reached the hanging foot,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7905.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and yet not quite.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7906.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She fell back,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7907.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and lay there howling,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7909.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the black blood flowing from her mouth.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7911.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he drew near,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7912.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7913.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|knowing that she was hurt,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7914.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now all the place was filled with groans and choking howls,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7918.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as the wolves rolled over and over beneath him who sat above,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7923.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The she-wolf grew faint,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7924.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|lest when he had killed her he should kill me also.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7927.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So I lifted the Watcher and sprang into the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_793.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So, when my mother heard the speech of Unandi she sprang up in anger.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7930.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|having it in my mind to slay the wolf before he lifted up his head.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7934.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But he heard my footsteps, or perhaps my shadow fell upon him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7939.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Loosing his grip, he looked up, this father of wolves;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7942.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then, making no sound, he sprang straight at my throat.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7946.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I saw him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7947.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and whirling the Watcher aloft,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7949.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I smote with all my strength.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7951.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it fell full on his chest and struck him backwards to the earth.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7955.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But there he would not stay,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7956.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|once more he sprang at me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7958.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the blow fell upon his right leg and broke it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7961.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that he could spring no more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7963.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet he ran at me on three feet,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7966.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he seized me with his teeth,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7967.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|biting through that leather bag,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7969.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|into the flesh behind.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7971.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I yelled with pain and rage,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7973.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and lifting the Watcher endways,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7975.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|drove it down with both hands,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7977.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as a man drives a stake into the earth,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_798.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|wife of a dog of a Zulu!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7980.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and that with so great a stroke that the skull of the wolf was shattered like a pot,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7986.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he fell dead,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7987.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|dragging me with him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7988.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|placing the handle of the Watcher between his jaws,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_799.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The woman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7991.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I forced them open,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7993.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|freeing my flesh from the grip of his teeth.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7995.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I looked at my wounds;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7997.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they were not deep,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_7998.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the leather bag had saved me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you have crowned their kings and shared their counsels,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_800.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who was very handsome,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8000.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet I feel them to this hour,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8002.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for there is poison in the mouth of a wolf.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8005.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently I glanced up,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8006.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and saw that the she-wolf had found her feet again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8009.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and stood as though unhurt;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_801.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|waited till my mother had finished her angry words;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8011.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they cannot destroy each other.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8013.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and yet she did not look at me or on her dead mate,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8016.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and crept softly behind her,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8018.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|lifting the Watcher,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8020.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I dashed him down with all my strength.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8022.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The blow fell on her neck and broke it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8024.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that she rolled over and at once was dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8027.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then went to the mouth of the cave and looked out.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8030.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The sun was sinking:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8032.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I must bide this night,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8033.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I dared not wend towards the plains alone with the wolves and the ghosts.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8038.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And if I dared not go alone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_804.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then she looked up and spoke slowly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8040.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|how much less should I dare to go bearing with me him who sat in the cleft of the rock!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8045.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|here I must bide,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8046.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so I went out of the cave to the spring which flows from the rock on the right yonder and washed my wounds and drank.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8053.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I came back and sat in the mouth of the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8056.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and watched the light die away from the face of the world.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8060.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|While it was dying there was silence,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8062.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|came howlings of ghosts and wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8064.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|such howlings as we hear to-night!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8067.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was awful here in the mouth of the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8069.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and if I had known it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_807.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said my mother.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8071.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|should I have dared to close it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8073.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|leaving myself alone with the dead wolves and him whom the wolves had struggled to tear down?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8078.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She seemed to grin at me, and, oh!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_808.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We are thirsty with long travel;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8081.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I grew afraid,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8082.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a place where spirits perch like vultures in a tree,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8086.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as they sweep round and round the world.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8088.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I went back to the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8090.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and feeling that I must do something lest I should go mad,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8093.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|taking my knife of iron,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8095.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I began to skin it by the light of the moon.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8098.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|For an hour or more I skinned,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_81.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You who overshadowed all peoples and took charge of them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_810.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|will you not, then, give us a cup of water?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8100.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|singing to myself as I worked,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8102.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and striving to forget him who sat in the cleft above and the howlings which ran about the mountains.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8108.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But ever the moonlight shone more clearly into the cave:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8112.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|now by it I could see his shape of bone and skin,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8115.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and even the bandage about his eyes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8118.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Why had he tied it there?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8119.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I wondered-perhaps to hide the faces of the fierce wolves as they sprang upwards to grip him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8125.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there before me glared two red eyes:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8128.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|With a yell, I lifted the Watcher and smote.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_813.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We have found none for many hours.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8131.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and something galloped away into the shadows.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8133.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the skin was off.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8135.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|now they fell upon it and rent it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8137.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|fighting horribly till all was finished.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8140.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Did I sleep or did I wake?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8142.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nay, I cannot tell.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8144.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I know this, that of a sudden I seemed to look up and see.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8147.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|shining upon him that sat aloft at the end of the cave.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_815.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will not, wife of a dog; go and seek water for yourself.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8151.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was a red light,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8152.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he glowed in it as glows a thing that is rotten.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8155.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|or seemed to look,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8157.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and then I thought that the hanging jaw moved,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8160.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and from it came a voice that was harsh and hollow as of one who speaks from an empty belly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8166.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|through a withered throat.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8168.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|what dost thou here in the Ghost Mountain,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8170.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8171.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|or seemed to answer,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8172.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I do this on the Ghost Mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8175.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I come to seek thy bones and bear them to thy mother for burial.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8179.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till the rock grew smooth beneath the wearing of their feet.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8183.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|being yet alive,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8184.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|watching the moon and the sun and the stars,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8187.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and learning the wisdom of the old witch who sits above in everlasting stone.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_819.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The woman's eyes filled with tears,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8193.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thine also shall be the wisdom of the old witch who sits aloft forever,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8199.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|These are not wolves that thou hast seen,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8201.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they are ghosts-evil ghosts of men who lived in ages gone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8207.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and who must now live till they be slain by men.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_821.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the boy folded his arms on his breast and scowled.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8211.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And knowest thou how they lived,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8213.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|When the light comes again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8214.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There shalt thou see how these men lived.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8218.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till they are led forth to die at the hands of men.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8221.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he whom thou hast slain was the king of them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8225.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she at his side was their queen.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8228.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thou shalt be king of the ghost-wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8231.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|whom a lion shall bring thee.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8233.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the wolves shall follow thee;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8235.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|all the three hundred and sixty and three of them that are left,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8239.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bringing you victory till all are dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8242.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that was an ill gift thou tookest from my mother-the gift of the Watcher,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8248.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bearing the Watcher,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8249.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|thou shalt thyself be slain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_825.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He was a very handsome boy,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8251.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on the morrow carry me back to my mother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8255.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that I may sleep where the ghost-wolves leap no more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8259.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have spoken, Galazi.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8261.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till at the last I could scarcely hear his words,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8264.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet I answered him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8265.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that the lion shall bring to me to rule with me over the ghost-wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_827.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with bright black eyes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8270.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I am the son of Mopo,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8271.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Lion of the Zulu;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8272.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if it was no dream,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8274.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered Galazi the Wolf.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8275.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Perhaps I dreamed, or perhaps the Dead One lied;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8279.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if he lied in this matter,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_828.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but when he scowled his eyes were like the sky before a thunderstorm.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8280.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|in other matters he did not lie,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8282.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as you shall hear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8283.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|or had dreamed that I heard them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8285.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I slept indeed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8287.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the grey light glinted upon the face of her who sits in stone above.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8291.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now I remembered the dream that I had dreamed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8294.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and leaving the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8295.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and as I went the rays of the sun lit upon her face,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8298.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I rejoiced to see them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8300.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the likeness to the face of a woman faded away,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8303.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I saw nothing before me but rugged heaps of piled-up rock.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8308.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|is the way of witches,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8309.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|be they of stone or flesh-when you draw near to them they change their shape.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8314.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a crack in the stone thrice as wide as a man can jump,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8318.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and near this crack stood great stones blackened by fire,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8322.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I looked down into the crack-it was very deep,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8325.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and green with moss,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8327.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and tall ferns grew about in it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8329.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the damp gathered there.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_833.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8331.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There was nothing else.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8332.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I had dreamed a lying dream.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8334.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and climbed down into the cleft,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8337.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|pushing aside the ferns.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8338.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Beneath the ferns was moss; I scraped it away with the Watcher.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_834.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"we are not wanted here any more than we were wanted yonder,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8343.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently the iron of the club struck on something that was yellow and round like a stone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8348.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and from the yellow thing came a hollow sound.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8350.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I dug deeper and scraped away more moss, till presently I saw.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8355.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Beneath the moss was nothing but the bones of men-old bones that had lain there many years;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8361.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the little ones had rotted,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8363.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and others still white.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8364.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They were not broken,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8366.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet on some of them I could see the marks of teeth.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8369.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now when I was come to the cave I did this:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_837.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Yes, let us be going, my son,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8371.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I skinned the she-wolf also.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8373.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|When I had finished the sun was up, and I knew that it was time to go.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8378.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I could not go alone-he who sat aloft in the cleft of the cave must go with me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8383.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who had spoken to me in a dream;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8385.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet I must do it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8387.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So I brought stones and piled them up till I could reach him;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_839.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered Unandi;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8391.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then I lifted him down,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8392.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for he was very light,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8394.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|being but skin and bones.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8396.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I bound the hides of the wolves about me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8399.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then leaving the leather bag,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_840.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the path is long, we are weary and shall fall by the way.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8400.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|into which he could not enter,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8402.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I took the Dead One and placed him on my shoulders as a man might carry a child,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8407.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Down the slope I went as swiftly as I could,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8410.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|when there came a rush of wings,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8412.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and a great eagle swept down at that which sat upon my shoulders.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8416.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the eagle flew away,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8417.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then I entered the dark of the forest.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8420.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Here I must walk softly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8422.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I heard a wolf howl on my right,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8424.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and from the left came answering howls,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8427.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I walked on boldly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8428.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I dared not stay,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8430.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|guiding myself by the sun,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8432.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which from time to time shone down on me redly through the boughs of the great trees.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8437.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|sniffing at the air as they went,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8439.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and now I came to a little open place,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_844.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I heard, and something pulled at my heart;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8441.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|behold!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8442.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|all the wolves in the world were gathered together there.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8445.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My heart melted, my legs trembled beneath me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8449.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|On every side were the brutes, great and hungry.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8452.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and slowly they crept up,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8454.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|muttering and growling as they came,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8457.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till they formed a deep circle round me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8459.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet they did not spring on me, only drew nearer and ever nearer.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8464.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently one sprang, indeed, but not at me;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8467.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he sprang at that which sat upon my shoulders.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_847.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I was sorry for the woman and her boy, they looked so tired.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8470.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he missed his aim,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8472.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|coming to the ground again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8473.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|stood there growling and whining like a beast afraid.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8476.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I remembered the words of my dream,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8479.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|how that the Dead One had given me wisdom that I should be king of the ghost-wolves-I and another whom a lion should bear to me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8487.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|For a moment I stood thinking,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8489.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then I lifted up my voice and howled like a wolf,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8492.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and lo!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8493.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I stretched out my hand and called to them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8495.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They ran to me, gathering round me as though to devour me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8499.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But they did not harm me;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_85.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Help of the fatherless when in trouble!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8501.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and fighting to come near me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8503.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|snatched at him who sat on my shoulder,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8505.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I struck him with the Watcher and he slunk back like a whipped hound;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_851.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|without saying anything to my mother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8510.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|moreover, the others bit him so that he yelled.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8513.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now I knew that I had no more to fear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8516.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I was king of the ghost-wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8518.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so I walked on,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8519.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with me came all the great pack of them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8522.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I walked on and on,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8524.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they trotted beside me silently,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8526.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the fallen leaves crackled beneath their feet,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_853.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I knew that there was a spring.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8530.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the dust rose up about them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8532.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till at length I reached the edge of the forest.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8535.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now I remembered that I must not be seen thus by men,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8538.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|lest they should think me a wizard and kill me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8541.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|at the edge of the forest I halted and made signs to the wolves to go back.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8545.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At this they howled piteously,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8548.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as though in grief,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8549.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I called to them that I would come again and be their king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_855.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently I came back with the gourd full of water.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8553.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then they all went, still howling, till presently I was alone.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8558.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8559.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on the morrow night,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8560.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I passed on till I came to the river;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8562.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it was still full,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8563.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the water had run down a little,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8565.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I waded into the river,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8567.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|using the Watcher as a staff,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8569.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the stream reached to my elbows,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8571.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but no higher.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8572.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now one on the farther bank of the river saw that which sat upon my shoulders,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8576.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and saw also the wolf's skin on my head,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8579.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who could not walk so far.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_858.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My mother wanted to catch me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8581.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But when they saw me coming up the slope of the hill,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8583.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and when they knew what it was that sat upon my shoulders,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8587.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they were smitten with fear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8588.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet they did not run,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_859.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I ran past her and gave the gourd to the boy.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8590.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because of their great wonder,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8592.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|only they walked backward before me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8594.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|clinging each to each and saying nothing.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8597.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I too came on silently,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8598.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and before its gates sat the old woman basking in the sun of the afternoon.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8603.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that you walk backwards like men bewitched,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8606.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|saying no word,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8607.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the little children clinging to the women,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8610.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the women clinging to the men,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8611.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till they had passed the old wife and ranged themselves behind her like a regiment of soldiers.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8617.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I came on to the old woman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8619.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and lifted him who sat upon my shoulders,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_862.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then my mother ceased trying to interfere,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8622.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|here is your son;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8623.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which I could not find.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8625.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Take him now and bury him, for I weary of his fellowship.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8628.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then she screamed aloud a shrill scream,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8631.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|whom for twice ten years and half a ten I have not looked upon.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8636.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now shalt thou find burial,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8638.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I with thee-ay,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8641.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|standing upon her feet with arms outstretched.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8643.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she fell forward upon the body of her son,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8646.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and was dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8647.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now silence came upon the place again, for all were fearful.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_865.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|only she beat the woman with her tongue all the while,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8651.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At last one cried:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8653.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|This is no man, my brothers, but a wolf.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8655.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I will bring wolves and ghosts upon you ere all is done.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8659.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now as I ran I met a girl;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8661.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a basket of mealies was on her head,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8663.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she bore a dead kid in her hand.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8665.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I snatched the mealies from her head and the kid from her hand.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8669.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I fled on,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8670.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and for that night I hid myself in the rocks beyond,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8673.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|On the morrow at dawn I rose and shook the dew from the wolf-hide.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8677.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I went on into the forest and howled like a wolf.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_868.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she felt in her heart that more evil would come upon us from her son.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8681.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the ghost-wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8682.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and howled in answer from far and near.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8684.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then I heard the pattering of their feet,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8686.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I counted their number;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8688.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they numbered three hundred and sixty and three.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8691.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I have become a wolf-man.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8692.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they know me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8693.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|now you are strong again,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8695.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I am young in years,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8696.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|before a man could count his fingers twice there would be little enough left of you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_87.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|PREFACE The writer of this romance has been encouraged to his task by a purpose somewhat beyond that of setting out a wild tale of savage life.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8701.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and see that the fastenings do not burst,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8703.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|lest it be the worse for you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8704.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and its teeth gleamed upon his head,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8707.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he took a spear in his hand.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8709.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Galazi also bound on the hide of the king of the wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8713.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they went out on to the space before the cave.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8716.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the moonlight fell upon him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8718.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and his teeth grinned beneath his curling lips.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8721.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But before ever the echoes had died in the air,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8725.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|from the heights of the rocks above and the depths of the forest beneath,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8729.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there came howlings in answer.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_873.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the gardens of my people would not now be a wilderness,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8731.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nearer they grew and nearer;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8733.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|now there was a sound of feet,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8735.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|great and grey,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8736.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bounded towards them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8738.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and after him many another.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8739.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They came to Galazi,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8741.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they sprang upon him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8742.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|fawning round him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8744.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but he beat them down with the Watcher.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8746.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Be not afraid!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8747.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"shall I learn to fear them now?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8749.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet though he spoke boldly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8751.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|in his heart he was afraid,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8753.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for this was the most terrible of all sights.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8756.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|from before and from behind,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8758.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that in a breath he was well-nigh hidden by their forms.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_876.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Unandi's son,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8762.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet no fang pierced him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8764.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the she-wolves gathered round him who wore the she-wolf's skin.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8768.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They were great and gaunt and hungry,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_877.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|having taken the gourd,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8771.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|all were full-grown,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8772.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there were no little ones,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8774.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and their number was so many that he could not count them in the moonlight.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8778.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|looking into their red eyes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_878.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|did not offer the water to his mother.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8780.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|felt his heart become as the heart of a wolf,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8783.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|lifted up his head and howled,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8785.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the she-wolves howled in answer.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8788.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"The pack is gathered; now for the hunt!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8790.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He spoke and bounded forward,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8793.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They fled down the mountain sides,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8795.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|holding up the Watcher,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8797.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I smell a quarry,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8798.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"in, my people, in!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8799.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|before them stood a buffalo,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8801.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a bull who lowed fiercely and sniffed the air.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8804.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|see, he is gaunt and thin!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8807.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that meat is tender which my people have hunted to the death!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_881.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He drank two-thirds of it himself;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8810.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The bull saw also,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8812.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and dashed down the hill,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8813.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with them all their company,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8816.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the rocks shook with the music of their hunting.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8819.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They rushed down the mountain side,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8821.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They rushed madly, yet his feet were swift as the swiftest;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8825.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|no wolf could outstrip him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8827.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in him was but one desire-the desire of prey.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_883.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I think that he would have drunk it all had not his thirst been slaked;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8831.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now they neared the borders of the forest, and Galazi shouted.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8835.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and these four leaped forward from the pack,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8838.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|running so swiftly that their bellies seemed to touch the ground.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8842.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|turning him from the forest and setting his head up the slope of the mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8846.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the chase wheeled,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8848.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the bull leaped and bounded up the mountain side,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8851.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|while behind came the Wolf-Brethren,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8854.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Up the hill they sped,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8856.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|his breath did not fail him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8858.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He ran so swiftly that the wolves were left behind,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8862.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|since here for a space the ground was level to his feet.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8865.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You do not run so ill, my brother, who have been sick of late.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8869.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Who shall touch the quarry first?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_887.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but when he had done he gave what was left to his mother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8871.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Good!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8872.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They sped forward with a bound,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8875.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|only the bull grew nearer and nearer.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8877.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he put out his strength and the swiftness of his feet, and lo!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8882.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|when he looked again he was alone, and the bull was very near.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8886.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now he reached the bull as he laboured on.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8889.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he lifted the spear in his hand,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_889.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she finished it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8892.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and of a sudden the great buffalo staggered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8895.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and fell dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8896.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Galazi came up.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8898.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Who now is the swiftest, Galazi?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8900.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Never did a man run as you run, nor ever shall again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8904.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they rested awhile.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8905.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So they cut meat from the bull,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8908.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|fighting furiously.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8909.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In a little while nothing was left except the larger bones,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_891.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and came forward,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8914.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and yet each wolf had but a little.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8917.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then they went back to the cave and slept.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_892.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|holding it in one hand;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8920.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and rule with him over the wolf-kind,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8923.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she tarries with the Halakazi.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8924.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he said that it should be so,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8927.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and on the morrow they made them blood-brethren,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_893.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|in the other he carried a short stick.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8930.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|to be one till death,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8931.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|before all the company of ghost-wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8934.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the wolves howled when they smelt the blood of men.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8937.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In all things thenceforth these two were equal,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8941.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And on many a moonlight night they and the wolves hunted together,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8946.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|winning their food.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8947.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At times they crossed the river,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8949.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|hunting in the plains,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8951.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|hearing the mighty howling,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8953.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then they would say that the ghosts were abroad and creep into their huts shivering with fear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8959.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But as yet the Wolf-Brethren and their pack killed no men,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_896.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What is your name, boy?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8963.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but game only,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8965.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on a night he dreamed of Nada,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8967.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and what had befallen me and her whom he deemed his mother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_897.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said to me as a big rich man speaks to one who is little and poor.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8971.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and his other brethren.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8973.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So he clothed himself,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8974.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|hiding his nakedness,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8976.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and there gave it out that he was a young man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8979.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who sought a wife.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8980.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though they held that his look was fierce and wild,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8983.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Galazi the Wizard.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8984.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But another answered that this was not Galazi,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8987.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for their eyes had seen him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8989.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and little of wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8991.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At first he would have spoken to them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8993.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who trembled with fear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8995.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|asked the captain what was his will.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8997.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the captain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_8998.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We are sent by the king to search for a certain youth,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9001.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Mopo gave it out that the youth was killed by a lion near these mountains,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9006.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"We know nothing of the youth,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9007.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Only this,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9008.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the captain,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9009.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|to kill him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9010.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"That is yet to do,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9012.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the captain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9013.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and a great anger burned in his breast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9016.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|was dead with the rest of his house,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9018.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he loved me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_902.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Mopo is my name,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9020.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But he said nothing;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9021.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|watching till none were looking,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9023.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he slipped past the backs of the captains and won the door of the hut.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9028.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|running swiftly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9029.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|crossed the river and came to the Ghost Mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_903.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9032.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the captain said that this could not be the lad,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9035.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"There is another youth,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9036.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a stranger, fierce, strong and tall, with eyes that shine like spears.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_904.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"And what is the name of your people?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9041.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Now this youth is fled,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9043.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the headman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9044.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and yet none saw him fly!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9046.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Perhaps he also is a wizard!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9048.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Indeed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9049.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have heard that now there are two of them upon the Ghost Mountain,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9052.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and that they hunt there at night with the ghost-wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9055.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I do not know if it is true.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9057.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Now I am minded to kill you,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9059.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because you have suffered this youth to escape me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_906.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Very well, Mopo; now I will tell you my name.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9062.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"It is no fault of mine,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9064.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|These young men are wizards, who can pass hither and thither at will.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9067.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I say this to you,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9069.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|captain of the king,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9070.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if you will go on the Ghost Mountain,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9072.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you must go there alone with your soldiers,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9075.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Yet I shall dare to-morrow,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9077.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the captain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9078.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There men do not fear spears or ghosts or wild beasts or magic,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9082.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but they fear the king's word alone.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9085.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The sun sets-give us food.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9087.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|To-morrow we will search the mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9089.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and when he had passed the forest-of which he had learned every secret way-the darkness gathered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_909.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And I will tell you something more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9095.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the wolves awoke in the darkness and drew near howling.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9099.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the brute did not know him, and flew at him, growling.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9103.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|when the wolves slept,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9104.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he might pass to and fro without the skin,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9107.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|at night it was not so.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9109.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|lest they should know him for one of the Wolf-Brethren,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_911.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I shall grow big, so big that my head will be lost in the clouds;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9112.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and it had not been his plan to seek the mountain again that night,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9116.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but rather on the morrow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9117.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but others were behind him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9119.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the wolves gathered fast.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9121.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he bounded away towards the cave,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9124.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though they pressed him hard,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9125.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Never before did he run so fast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9127.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and as he did so the wolves dashed themselves against it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9132.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he clad himself in the hide of the she-wolf,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9135.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|pushing aside the stone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9136.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And, lo!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9137.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the eyes of the wolves were opened,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9140.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they knew him for one of the brethren who ruled over them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9144.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and slunk away at his bidding.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9146.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he thought.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9147.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"You have run a great risk, my brother,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9149.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|these people of ours are hungry for the flesh of men;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9152.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and all my brethren who are dead,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9154.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the wives of Mopo.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9155.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"That will be merry, my brother,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9157.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I long to look upon that captain as a maid longs for her lover's kiss.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_916.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you will look up and you shall not see it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9162.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But first let us rest and eat, for the night is young;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9165.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So they rested and ate,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9167.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and afterwards went out armed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9169.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Galazi moved among them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9171.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|shaking the Watcher,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9173.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as they sat upon their haunches,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9174.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and followed him with their fiery eyes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9177.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"We do not hunt game to-night, little people,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9180.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now all the wolves howled as though they understood.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9184.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the pack divided itself as was its custom,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9187.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in silence they moved swiftly down towards the plain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_919.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My face will blind you;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9191.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They came to the river and swam it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9193.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|eight spear throws away,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9195.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the Wolf-Brethren took counsel together,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9198.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|went to the north gate,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9199.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They reached them safely and in silence,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9202.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for at the bidding of the brethren the wolves ceased from their howlings.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9206.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the brethren pulled out the thorns and made a passage.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_921.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it will be bright like the sun;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9210.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and awakening,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9211.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the wind blew from that quarter.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9213.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|These dogs ran out barking,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9216.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who pulled away the thorns.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9218.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now when the wolves saw the dogs they could be restrained no longer,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9223.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but sprang on them and tore them to fragments,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9226.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that they sprang from sleep,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9228.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|snatching their arms.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_923.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and my people will grow great with me;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9230.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then they cried aloud in terror,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9232.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|saying that the ghosts were on them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9234.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|here also they met a man clad in a wolf's skin only,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9238.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with him countless wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9241.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|black and grey.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9242.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|some flung themselves to earth screaming in their fear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9246.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and some strove to run away,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9248.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the greater part of the soldiers,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_925.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they shall eat up the whole world.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9251.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|came together in knots,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9252.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and that though they shook with fear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9255.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they flung themselves upon the soldiers and the people of the kraal,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9259.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with them came the wolves.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9261.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Some were killed, but the rest did not stay.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9264.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently the knots of men broke up,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9267.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and to each man wolves hung by twos and threes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_927.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And when I am big and my people are big,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9270.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|dragging him to earth.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9272.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the wolves hunted them by gaze and scent,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9275.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The Wolf-Brethren also ravened with the rest.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9278.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Busy was the Watcher,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9280.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and many bowed beneath him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9282.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was finished;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9283.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the wolves growled sullenly as they took their fill,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9288.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they who had been hungry for many days.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9290.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the brethren met,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9292.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and laughed in their wolf joy,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9294.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because they had slaughtered those who were sent out to slaughter.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9298.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They called to the wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9299.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bidding them search the huts,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_930.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then I will remember your tribe-the tribe of the Langeni,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9301.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the wolves entered the huts as dogs enter a thicket,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9305.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and killed those who lurked there,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9308.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|or drove them forth to be slain without.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9311.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently a man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9312.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|great and tall,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9313.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|sprang from the last of the huts,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9315.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|where he had hidden himself,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9317.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the wolves outside rushed on him to drag him down.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9321.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He beat them back, and stalked up to the captain, saying:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9325.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|beneath the shadow of her who sits in stone?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9328.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on which the moon shone bright.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9330.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though he had hidden from the wolves,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9332.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and answered boldly:-
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9333.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|What is that to you, wizard?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9335.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let them make an end of me also.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9337.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And he looked at the wolves tearing their prey, and shuddered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_934.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who would not give me and my mother a cup of milk when we were weary.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9341.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Say, captain,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9342.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|drawing back his hood of wolf's hide so that the moonlight fell upon his face,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9347.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"It is the face,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9348.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the captain, astonished.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9350.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it is the face.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9352.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And he pointed to the dead.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9354.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now choose, and swiftly.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9355.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Will you run for your life against my wolves?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9358.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Will you do battle for your life against these four?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9361.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who watched him with slavering lips;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9363.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|or will you stand face to face with me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9366.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with him who bears the club,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9367.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I fear ghosts, but of men I have no fear, though they be wizards,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9372.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the captain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9373.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Good!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9374.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bounding over the dead and the wolves who preyed upon them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9378.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the captain followed with uplifted spear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_938.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You see this gourd;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9381.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and mocked him as he came.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9383.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and always his eyes were on the earth.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9385.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Of a sudden,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9386.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|saw him sweep forward like a bird and stoop to the ground.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9391.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|there was an axe in his hand.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9393.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The captain rushed at him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9394.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the captain threw up his arms and fell to the earth.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9398.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and have found an axe to be slain by it!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_940.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for every drop it can hold the blood of a man shall flow-the blood of one of your men.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9401.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My brother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9402.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will fight no more with the spear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9404.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but with the axe alone;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9406.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it was to seek an axe that I ran to and fro like a coward.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9409.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But this is a poor thing!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9411.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which is called Groan-Maker,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9413.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|of which we have heard tell,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9415.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that axe and club may stand together in the fray.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9418.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"That must be for another night,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9420.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We have not done so ill for once.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9422.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|of which we stand in need,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9424.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and then to the mountain before dawn finds us.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9427.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and this was but the first of many deaths that they wrought with the help of the wolves.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9432.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they ate them up,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9434.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|till their name and the name of the ghost-wolves became terrible in the ears of men,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9439.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But they found that the wolves would not go abroad to worry everywhere.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9443.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|where dwelt the chief Jikiza,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9445.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then Galazi remembered the dream that he had dreamed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9449.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|in which the Dead One in the cave had seemed to speak,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9452.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|telling him that there only where the men-eaters had hunted in the past might the wolves hunt to-day.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9459.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So they returned home,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_946.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But because you gave me the water I will spare you,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9461.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he was a man full grown,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9463.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a man fierce and tall and keen;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9466.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a slayer of men,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9467.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But he was not yet named the Slaughterer,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9470.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the desire to win the axe was foremost in his mind,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9474.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|even that of good weapons.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9476.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and once as he lurked he saw a man great,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9479.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who bore upon his shoulder a shining axe,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9482.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|hafted with the horn of a rhinoceros.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9485.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and to Galazi he spoke of little else,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9488.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|wearying him much with his talk,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_949.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and you only,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9490.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But for all his longing he could find no means to win it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9494.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|whose skin shone like the copper anklets on her limbs.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9498.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She walked slowly towards the reeds where he lay hidden.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_950.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and make you great under me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9502.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nor did she stop at the brink of the reeds;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9504.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and at once began to weep,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9506.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|speaking to herself as she wept.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9508.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Would that the ghost-wolves might fall on him and all that is his,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9513.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she sobbed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9514.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I would hound them on, even if I myself must next know their fangs.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9518.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if I must wed him, I will give him a knife for the bride's kiss.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_952.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You shall grow fat in my shadow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9522.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and of a sudden reared himself up before the maid,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9526.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the she-wolf's fangs shone upon his brow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9529.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"The ghost-wolves are at hand, damsel,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9532.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9533.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They are ever at hand for those who need them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9535.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the maid saw him and screamed faintly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9538.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|wondering at the greatness and the fierce eyes of the man who spoke to her.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_954.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You alone I will never harm, however you sin against me; this I swear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9543.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I fear you not, whoever you are.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9545.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for all men fear me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9547.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I am one of the Wolf-Brethren, whose names have been told of;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9550.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Take heed, now, lest I kill you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9552.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It will be of little avail to call upon your people,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9555.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for my feet are fleeter than theirs.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9557.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I have no wish to call upon my people, Wolf-Man,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9561.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9562.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And for the rest, I am too young to kill.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9564.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"That is so, maiden,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9566.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Were they not fierce words, such as my heart likes well?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9569.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"It seems that you heard them,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9571.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the girl.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9572.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What need to waste breath in speaking them again?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9575.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|No need, maiden.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9576.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now tell me your story; perhaps I may find a way to help you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9580.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"There is little to tell,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9582.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9583.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It is a small tale and a common.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9585.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He married my mother, who is dead, but none of his blood is in me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9589.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|whom I hate,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_959.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But for that woman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9590.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because Masilo offers many cattle for me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9593.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Is there, then, another whom you would wed, maiden?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9596.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|If I die, I shall escape;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9598.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if Masilo dies, I shall escape;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_96.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|When he was yet a lad,-now some seventeen years ago,-fortune took him to South Africa.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9601.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|What of that wolf-people of yours, are they not hungry, Wolf-Man?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9605.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"I cannot bring them here,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9606.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"There is another way,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9607.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if one can be found to try it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9609.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And again she looked at him strangely,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_961.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he pointed to my mother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9612.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|causing the blood to beat within him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9614.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|do you not know how our people are governed?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9617.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He that can win the axe in war from the hand of him who holds it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9620.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|shall be our chief.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9622.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But if he who holds the axe dies unconquered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9625.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then his son takes his place and with it the axe.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9628.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he fell over,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9629.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|feigning death.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_963.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|let her make haste and die,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9630.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the owner of the axe laughed, and turned to walk away.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9634.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But the forefather of Jikiza sprang up behind him and pierced him through with a spear,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_964.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that I do not need to teach her what a long time death can take to come.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9640.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Does he, then, slay many?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9642.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|she said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9643.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for none dare stand against him-no, not with all to win.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9647.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he is unconquerable,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9648.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and to fight with him is sure death.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9650.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Fifty-and-one have tried in all,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9652.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|if it is stolen or found,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9654.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it has no virtue-nay,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9656.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it brings shame and death to him who holds it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9659.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he asked again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9660.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Once in every year,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9661.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on the first day of the new moon of the summer season,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9664.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now if one comes forward,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9666.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and there the matter is ended.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9668.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|when the head is hewn from his foe,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9670.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they talk as before.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9671.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|All are free to come to the meeting,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9673.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Perhaps I shall be there,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9675.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|After this meeting at the new moon,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9677.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I am to be given in marriage to Masilo,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9679.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the maid.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9680.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then he will be chief,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9681.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and knew that he had found favour in her sight;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9684.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"If perchance I should be there,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9686.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9687.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and rule over the People of the Axe,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9689.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you should not live far from the shadow of the axe thenceforward,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_969.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have spoken.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9693.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though some might not wish to dwell in that shadow;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9696.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but first you must win the axe.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9697.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Many have tried, and all have failed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_970.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And he ground his teeth and shook his stick towards us.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9700.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Yet one must succeed at last,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9702.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and swam it with great strokes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9704.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and love of him entered into her heart-a love that was fierce and jealous and strong.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9711.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though this has been his fate,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9713.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that women have brought sorrow on his head.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9716.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Fifteen days must pass before the day of the new moon,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9720.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he told Galazi something of the tale,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9722.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the matter might not stay there,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9724.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So the time wore on, and at length came the day of the new moon.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9729.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In his hand he took a stout fighting-shield,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9732.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which he had made of buffalo hide,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9734.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and then they moved together slowly down the mountain and crossed the river by a ford,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_974.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My mother stood silent awhile.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9740.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for he wished to save his strength.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9742.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|On the farther side of the river Galazi hid himself in the reeds,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9746.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because his face was known,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9748.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|not knowing if he should look upon him again.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9751.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he saw that many people were streaming through them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9754.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and mingled with the people.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9756.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently they came to the open space in front of the huts of Jikiza,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_976.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then she gasped out:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9760.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In the centre of them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9761.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and before a heap of the skulls of men which were piled up against his door-posts,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9766.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a huge man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9768.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a hairy and a proud,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9769.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who glared about him rolling his eyes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_977.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He speaks like a man, does he?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9772.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and each man as he came up saluted the axe,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9775.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and few took any notice of him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9777.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|except Zinita,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9779.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|on his right hand,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9780.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|is Masilo.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9781.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the marriage gift is not yet agreed on.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9784.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I demand a hundred head of cattle from Masilo,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9787.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for the maid is fair and straight,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9789.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a proper maid,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_979.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will teach him another note-the brat of an evil prophet!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9790.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my daughter,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9791.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though not of my blood.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9793.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But Masilo offers fifty head only, therefore I ask you to settle it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9798.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"We hear you, Lord of the Axe,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9800.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered one of the councillors,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9802.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you must on this day of the year,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9804.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Can I never have done in it?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9806.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and now for many years I have challenged,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9808.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|like a cock on a dunghill,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9810.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it shall be,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9811.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with it the chieftainship of the People of the Axe.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9814.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Thus he spoke very fast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9816.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Come forth from behind that big shield of yours,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9819.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_982.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and hit her so hard on the head that she fell down.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9820.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he looked so fierce,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9822.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though he was but young,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9823.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that the people laughed no more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9826.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9827.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as you must by the custom,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9828.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|When I have killed you I will take a name who now have none.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9832.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now once more the people laughed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9835.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and sprang up gasping.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9837.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you dare to speak thus to me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9840.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|to me the Unconquered,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9842.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the holder of the axe!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9843.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|People of the Axe,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9844.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He would stand in my place,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9846.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I tell you all,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9847.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that presently I will stand upon his head,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9850.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and then we will settle the matter of Masilo.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9853.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|or if you must babble,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9854.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|speak those words which you would say ere you bid the sun farewell.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9859.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the people found this sport-all except Masilo,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_986.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9863.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who looked askance at the stranger,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9865.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|tall and fierce,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9866.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and with no love.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9867.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and Galazi,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9869.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|seeing it from afar,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_987.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they were words of prophecy,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9870.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|could keep away no longer,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9872.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but drew near and mingled with the crowd.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9875.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they were set in its centre and there were ten paces between them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9879.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|looking at the weapons of the two,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_988.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they came true.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9881.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said an old man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9883.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The old man spoke thus in the hearing of Galazi the Wolf,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9887.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and Galazi thought that he spoke wisely,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9890.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9891.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the word was given,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9892.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for his rage was great.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9894.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then suddenly he leaped aside,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9897.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|making a great sound,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9899.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a shout of laughter went up from the hundreds of the people,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_990.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The last words I heard him speak were words of prophecy also,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9902.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Round he came like a bull that is mad,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9905.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who lifted his shield to meet him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9908.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|just when the great axe leapt on high,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9911.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now once more the shout of laughter went up,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9915.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and after him rushed Jikiza,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9917.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he ran keeping his back to the sun as much as might be,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9922.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that he might watch the shadow of Jikiza.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9925.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|while the people cheered the chase as hunters cheer a dog which pursues a buck.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_993.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I think that they will come true.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9930.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|yet he went ever faster and faster,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9933.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|suddenly he made as though he were about to fall himself,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9936.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and stumbled out of the path far to the right,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9940.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|caught his feet in the shield and fell headlong to earth.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9944.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Before men could so much as think,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9946.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and sprung back,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9948.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|holding the great axe aloft,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_995.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Even now they are coming true.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9950.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and casting down his own weapon upon the ground.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9954.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the watchers saw all the cunning of his fight,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9957.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But others were silent.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9959.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and examined its curved points of blue steel,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9962.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the beauty of its haft,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9964.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|bound about with wire of brass,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9967.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and ending in a knob like the knob of a stick,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_997.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In the one he told how the Zulu people should rise.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9970.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as a lover looks upon the beauty of his bride.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9973.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then before all men he kissed the broad blade and cried aloud:-
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9978.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|whom I have won in war.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9980.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Never shall we part,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9982.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I am not minded that others should handle thee when I am gone.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9986.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Thus he cried in the hearing of men,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9989.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then turned to Jikiza,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9991.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who stood weeping,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9992.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|because he had lost all.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9994.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Fight on.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9995.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You are as well armed as I was a while ago,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/3hours/6097_9998.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|when I did not fear to stand before you.
